1
00:02:28,979 --> 00:02:30,771
No.

2
00:02:31,854 --> 00:02:33,687
It's off-key.

3
00:02:34,354 --> 00:02:37,271
I'm telling you, it's off-key.
Play it again.

4
00:02:37,354 --> 00:02:38,437
Oh, God!

5
00:02:39,687 --> 00:02:41,354
Let it be.

6
00:02:41,604 --> 00:02:44,729
-Why are you nagging him?
-The piano's out of tune.

7
00:02:45,521 --> 00:02:46,729
-Here.
-Play it, come on.

8
00:02:46,896 --> 00:02:51,479
Take this. You are not well.
Get some rest, okay?

9
00:02:51,854 --> 00:02:54,771
Saksham, it's quite late.
You should go home.

10
00:02:54,854 --> 00:02:56,562
No, sit down.

11
00:02:56,687 --> 00:02:57,562
But--

12
00:02:58,187 --> 00:03:02,479
-He's not playing it correctly.
-Teach him how to play it tomorrow.

13
00:03:02,562 --> 00:03:06,729
No, you mustn't stop until you learn
to play a musical instrument properly.

14
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:08,854
You must respect it.

15
00:03:09,646 --> 00:03:11,437
Otherwise, the notes will be mad.

16
00:03:12,812 --> 00:03:16,687
Even if you play one note incorrectly,
it'll affect the entire tune.

17
00:03:17,562 --> 00:03:19,562
-Come on, play it--
-Do as you please!

18
00:03:20,187 --> 00:03:21,771
You never listen to me!

19
00:03:22,229 --> 00:03:23,896
You've turned the house into a junkyard!

20
00:03:24,187 --> 00:03:25,771
And what's with this gigantic piano!

21
00:03:26,396 --> 00:03:30,104
You're not well,
so I have to do all the cleaning!

22
00:03:30,187 --> 00:03:31,896
Whatever!

23
00:03:33,312 --> 00:03:36,812
Grandpa, I'll come tomorrow
and play the tune properly.

24
00:03:36,896 --> 00:03:41,146
Its notes are out of tune.
It must be restrung.

25
00:03:41,396 --> 00:03:44,521
-Okay, Grandpa. I'll restring it tomorrow.
-Okay.

26
00:03:44,646 --> 00:03:46,437
-Good night.
-Good night, son.

27
00:03:46,729 --> 00:03:50,021
-Good night, Grandma!
-Good night! Go home now!

28
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:52,687
Who wants to live here, anyway!

29
00:03:53,062 --> 00:03:55,271
We're just stuck here.

30
00:03:55,854 --> 00:03:57,854
He's obsessed with--

31
00:03:57,937 --> 00:04:03,562
Damn music! What a pain in the neck!

32
00:04:04,604 --> 00:04:06,937
Here we go! He won't give up.

33
00:04:09,812 --> 00:04:10,854
What happened?

34
00:04:12,687 --> 00:04:13,687
Did you fall?

35
00:04:14,021 --> 00:04:15,021
What--

36
00:04:16,646 --> 00:04:19,562
Hey, Saksham! Look what happened to him!

37
00:04:21,354 --> 00:04:23,354
What happened to you?

38
00:04:23,729 --> 00:04:25,479
-Saksham, look what happened to him!
-Grandpa!

39
00:04:25,562 --> 00:04:28,396
-What happened to you?
-Grandpa!

40
00:04:28,479 --> 00:04:29,479
Please, wake up!

41
00:04:39,646 --> 00:04:40,979
It's right here.

42
00:04:41,729 --> 00:04:43,146
-We're here.
-Take the suitcase.

43
00:04:43,854 --> 00:04:44,812
Be careful.

44
00:04:46,187 --> 00:04:47,021
Let's go.

45
00:04:47,104 --> 00:04:50,229
-You remember what I had told you, right?
-Namaste.

46
00:04:50,312 --> 00:04:53,062
You have got my ball, right?
I had told you to pack it.

47
00:04:53,187 --> 00:04:54,354
Keep quiet!

48
00:04:54,437 --> 00:04:56,104
Pankaj is the third brother.

49
00:04:56,854 --> 00:04:59,729
-Isn't the other brother coming?
-The younger son must be on his way.

50
00:04:59,812 --> 00:05:00,937
We've informed him.

51
00:05:01,312 --> 00:05:02,479
Everyone's working now.

52
00:05:02,562 --> 00:05:04,062
-Namaste, Auntie.
-Namaste, Auntie.

53
00:05:04,146 --> 00:05:05,187
Pankaj is here.

54
00:05:06,687 --> 00:05:07,729
Namaste, Uncle.

55
00:05:08,812 --> 00:05:10,354
-Hello, Uncle.
-Hello.

56
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:13,021
How are you?

57
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:15,229
-God bless you.
-Come inside.

58
00:05:15,312 --> 00:05:16,646
How are you, son? God bless you.

59
00:05:17,187 --> 00:05:18,187
He's his son.

60
00:05:23,729 --> 00:05:24,729
Namaste.

61
00:05:26,771 --> 00:05:28,187
Dad is no more.

62
00:05:36,479 --> 00:05:37,521
Come on. Hug me.

63
00:05:43,146 --> 00:05:44,604
-I'll just go and talk to Mom.
-Sure.

64
00:05:44,896 --> 00:05:45,937
He's gained weight.

65
00:05:46,271 --> 00:05:48,479
-Are you talking about me?
-No, I'm talking about Pankaj.

66
00:05:48,562 --> 00:05:49,687
-Oh.
-He's gained weight.

67
00:05:49,771 --> 00:05:50,604
Yeah.

68
00:06:10,437 --> 00:06:12,687
Brother-in-law has left us, son.

69
00:06:28,437 --> 00:06:31,187
Let's go to that room. Put on your shoes.

70
00:06:31,354 --> 00:06:32,729
-Here.
-Come on, let's go.

71
00:06:32,812 --> 00:06:34,937
-Are you hungry?
-I'll get you something to eat.

72
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:36,979
He got lucky.

73
00:06:38,062 --> 00:06:39,062
Come on, open it.

74
00:06:39,646 --> 00:06:41,771
-Panditji, will this do?
-Yes.

75
00:06:42,104 --> 00:06:44,937
-Okay, then.
-You should get it checked.

76
00:06:45,021 --> 00:06:47,104
-I think he's applied some powder.
-It's your old--

77
00:06:47,562 --> 00:06:50,521
-What about the rest of the stuff?
-How many knots am I supposed to tie?

78
00:06:51,521 --> 00:06:52,771
-Tell me!
-Three.

79
00:06:54,312 --> 00:06:57,437
Pankaj… you should have
worn white clothes.

80
00:06:59,104 --> 00:07:00,146
Never mind.

81
00:07:04,812 --> 00:07:05,771
Hasn't Neetu come yet?

82
00:07:07,271 --> 00:07:08,812
His flight got a bit delayed.

83
00:07:09,437 --> 00:07:10,604
He'll get here by 4:00 p.m.

84
00:07:12,312 --> 00:07:13,271
How did you get here?

85
00:07:14,979 --> 00:07:15,937
-By bus.
-Yes!

86
00:07:16,771 --> 00:07:19,562
-Train bookings were full…
-It's right there on top!

87
00:07:19,646 --> 00:07:20,771
Let it be, I'll get it.

88
00:07:21,354 --> 00:07:22,896
…because of the Christmas holidays.

89
00:07:23,937 --> 00:07:26,646
Holiday or no holiday,
getting a train ticket is tough.

90
00:07:27,687 --> 00:07:28,771
We came by taxi.

91
00:07:29,687 --> 00:07:31,854
-By taxi.
-From so far?

92
00:07:31,937 --> 00:07:32,854
Let's go.

93
00:07:33,479 --> 00:07:35,396
They got here on time,
that's what matters.

94
00:07:36,687 --> 00:07:38,937
-Uncle, namaste.
-God bless you.

95
00:07:41,187 --> 00:07:42,187
When did you arrive?

96
00:07:45,437 --> 00:07:46,937
I was the first one to arrive.

97
00:07:49,396 --> 00:07:52,729
I set out…
as soon as your mother called.

98
00:07:52,812 --> 00:07:54,687
Let's go. We have to buy some vegetables.

99
00:07:54,771 --> 00:07:56,521
I knew you'd be late.

100
00:07:57,437 --> 00:07:58,604
After all, she's my sister.

101
00:07:58,687 --> 00:08:00,104
-Work is inevitable, right?
-Yes.

102
00:08:00,396 --> 00:08:02,979
Uncle, it's good that you
came, otherwise--

103
00:08:03,521 --> 00:08:04,812
Otherwise?

104
00:08:05,521 --> 00:08:07,521
It would've been very difficult.

105
00:08:07,729 --> 00:08:10,437
-Right.
-Uncle, you must be tired. Have a seat.

106
00:08:10,521 --> 00:08:13,771
I haven't come here to sit, Gajraj.
There's so much work to be done.

107
00:08:14,604 --> 00:08:17,021
We're here now, Uncle.
Please, get some rest.

108
00:08:17,146 --> 00:08:19,937
What about Neetu? Where is he?
When is he coming?

109
00:08:20,021 --> 00:08:24,771
I just told you his flight got delayed.
He'll be here soon.

110
00:08:24,854 --> 00:08:27,604
-Yes.
-Is there only one flight from Mumbai?

111
00:08:27,854 --> 00:08:28,896
His father just died.

112
00:08:30,479 --> 00:08:35,521
Uncle… he knows that his father just died.
He'll be here soon.

113
00:08:35,604 --> 00:08:37,521
You live nearby, in Raebareli,

114
00:08:37,896 --> 00:08:39,521
-but he's coming from Mumbai.
-Someone, get me water!

115
00:08:39,604 --> 00:08:40,771
-Can't you understand?
-Hey!

116
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:41,729
Who said--

117
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,812
-Brother-in-law, you're here!
-Please, come.

118
00:08:44,271 --> 00:08:45,354
When did you arrive?

119
00:08:45,437 --> 00:08:48,521
When? I've been sitting
here alone for hours.

120
00:08:48,937 --> 00:08:50,562
I got here before you did.

121
00:08:51,729 --> 00:08:53,729
Yeah, you got here about
seven minutes before me.

122
00:08:53,812 --> 00:08:56,479
-I got here an hour before you.
-Did you hear him?

123
00:08:56,687 --> 00:08:59,104
-We came together.
-You two came at the same time.

124
00:08:59,187 --> 00:09:00,021
Yeah, but--

125
00:09:00,104 --> 00:09:01,396
-Neetu is here.
-Neetu is here.

126
00:09:01,479 --> 00:09:04,062
-He's finally here.
-Hey, check it once just to be sure.

127
00:09:04,396 --> 00:09:05,396
He's come alone.

128
00:09:05,479 --> 00:09:07,521
-Namaste, Uncle Neetu.
-His wife didn't come with him.

129
00:09:07,604 --> 00:09:08,437
Let me get that.

130
00:09:08,521 --> 00:09:11,396
It doesn't matter. He's here.
Let him see his mother first.

131
00:09:14,354 --> 00:09:16,562
-I don't want to do it.
-There's no other way, right?

132
00:09:17,396 --> 00:09:18,812
-Let's go, then.
-Where's Mom?

133
00:09:20,104 --> 00:09:22,146
Panditji, be quick.

134
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:24,604
Take your shoes off.

135
00:09:44,396 --> 00:09:47,146
Look, your favorite son is here.

136
00:09:49,354 --> 00:09:50,479
Control yourself.

137
00:09:52,521 --> 00:09:54,562
Hey, console your mother.

138
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:07,437
-Please, control yourself.
-Calm down, Mom.

139
00:10:09,771 --> 00:10:12,062
My son…

140
00:10:12,146 --> 00:10:14,562
Laali, it's getting late.

141
00:10:15,187 --> 00:10:16,979
-Yeah.
-We should go.

142
00:10:18,854 --> 00:10:19,937
-Hurry up!
-Mom.

143
00:10:20,021 --> 00:10:21,771
Dad is no more.

144
00:10:23,437 --> 00:10:24,646
Come on, get up.

145
00:10:39,521 --> 00:10:41,479
Wait. Wait for me.

146
00:10:41,812 --> 00:10:42,812
-Uncle!
-Uncle!

147
00:10:42,896 --> 00:10:45,021
How can he just leave us like that?

148
00:10:45,396 --> 00:10:46,771
-Ramprasad!
-Hey--

149
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,687
-Hey!
-Hey, careful!

150
00:10:48,771 --> 00:10:51,687
-Make him sit down.
-Let me help.

151
00:10:51,771 --> 00:10:52,896
Be careful.

152
00:10:52,979 --> 00:10:55,937
-Why did he come here all the way?
-Does he ever listen?

153
00:10:56,021 --> 00:10:58,729
-Why? Is he hard of hearing?
-No, I didn't mean that.

154
00:10:58,812 --> 00:11:01,312
I want to see his face
for my last memory.

155
00:11:01,521 --> 00:11:02,937
-He does as he pleases.
-Yes.

156
00:11:03,021 --> 00:11:03,896
Oh, okay.

157
00:11:04,312 --> 00:11:05,896
-Namaste.
-Get lost!

158
00:11:05,979 --> 00:11:08,646
-Why are you scolding him?
-I knew the car didn't have enough petrol,

159
00:11:08,729 --> 00:11:11,021
-but he said we'll push it if need be.
-And you brought him here.

160
00:11:11,104 --> 00:11:13,354
Our elder aunt is also here.
She is inside.

161
00:11:13,562 --> 00:11:15,562
-Is she still alive?
-Shut up.

162
00:11:15,646 --> 00:11:17,187
-Panditji!
-Yes?

163
00:11:17,437 --> 00:11:18,646
-Is everything ready?
-Yes.

164
00:11:18,729 --> 00:11:20,104
-Shall we carry him?
-Yes, let's go.

165
00:11:20,187 --> 00:11:22,771
-Uncle, wait a minute. I'll get Mom.
-Okay, go.

166
00:11:22,854 --> 00:11:24,104
Go, get her here.

167
00:11:26,104 --> 00:11:29,229
Mom… it's time.

168
00:11:29,646 --> 00:11:30,562
Let's go.

169
00:11:32,396 --> 00:11:33,229
Come.

170
00:11:51,937 --> 00:11:55,771
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

171
00:11:56,354 --> 00:12:00,687
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

172
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:05,437
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

173
00:12:05,729 --> 00:12:09,896
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

174
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:14,437
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

175
00:12:14,729 --> 00:12:19,271
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

176
00:12:20,021 --> 00:12:22,604
-How big is the house?
-It's huge!

177
00:12:23,396 --> 00:12:25,146
Yes, it's huge!

178
00:12:25,937 --> 00:12:27,812
We're a big family, after all.

179
00:12:28,562 --> 00:12:30,562
We won't fit into a tiny house.

180
00:12:30,687 --> 00:12:31,979
No more kids now.

181
00:12:32,521 --> 00:12:36,354
-But I want more.
-Hey, let go of me! Let go!

182
00:12:37,354 --> 00:12:39,479
Be quiet, all of you!

183
00:12:42,354 --> 00:12:46,479
Listen! Come home early this evening!

184
00:12:48,937 --> 00:12:51,021
We'll have dinner together!
I'll be waiting!

185
00:12:55,479 --> 00:12:56,979
I'll be back soon, Savitri.

186
00:13:09,229 --> 00:13:13,229
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

187
00:13:13,562 --> 00:13:17,104
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

188
00:13:18,229 --> 00:13:20,479
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

189
00:13:27,521 --> 00:13:30,687
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

190
00:13:31,896 --> 00:13:33,562
"Lord Ram's name is the truth."

191
00:13:35,854 --> 00:13:37,687
CHADMAL CREMATORIUM

192
00:13:47,646 --> 00:13:49,771
-How much does the wood cost?
-It's 400 rupees a ton.

193
00:13:49,937 --> 00:13:51,146
-Really?
-Yes!

194
00:13:51,229 --> 00:13:54,687
Back in our hometown,
we get it for 200 rupees.

195
00:13:54,771 --> 00:13:55,854
You're right, brother.

196
00:13:56,021 --> 00:13:57,687
Sir, it's the right price.

197
00:13:58,062 --> 00:14:00,354
Who bargains at a crematorium?

198
00:14:00,437 --> 00:14:01,271
What are you--

199
00:14:01,354 --> 00:14:03,062
He's right.
They're waiting for the wood.

200
00:14:03,146 --> 00:14:04,896
He wants 400 rupees a ton.

201
00:14:04,979 --> 00:14:07,396
-What does it matter!
-Who sent him to get the wood!

202
00:14:07,562 --> 00:14:10,146
-Go, Pankaj. Sort it out.
-I'll go.

203
00:14:10,229 --> 00:14:12,396
-Uncle--
-Someone, handle him.

204
00:14:12,479 --> 00:14:14,479
-What's our number?
-Lucky seven.

205
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,521
-Hurry up.
-He's saying it'd cost 400 rupees.

206
00:14:16,604 --> 00:14:18,687
-The day's about to end. Come on.
-Be quick!

207
00:14:18,771 --> 00:14:21,312
-Let's hurry up.
-Why are you bargaining?

208
00:14:21,396 --> 00:14:23,562
Take the dry bits.
Otherwise, it'll take time.

209
00:14:23,646 --> 00:14:26,187
-So what? Do you have to go somewhere?
-Let's go.

210
00:14:26,396 --> 00:14:28,062
-You--
-Ignore him, Uncle. Let it be.

211
00:14:28,146 --> 00:14:30,771
-What's he even saying!
-Come on, let's go.

212
00:14:51,312 --> 00:14:56,604
It's time to say goodbye

213
00:15:06,062 --> 00:15:11,896
Your soul is about to release
From your body

214
00:15:17,146 --> 00:15:22,979
No one knows where you are going

215
00:15:24,437 --> 00:15:30,396
No one will recognize your new face

216
00:15:31,687 --> 00:15:37,604
You will leave behind
All ties and bonds

217
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:42,437
O traveler, you'll take the path

218
00:15:42,521 --> 00:15:45,812
You must tread

219
00:15:50,354 --> 00:15:55,146
It's time to say goodbye

220
00:16:01,437 --> 00:16:06,771
Why must you depart?

221
00:16:10,646 --> 00:16:11,646
Auntie, wait.

222
00:16:13,729 --> 00:16:16,562
Hurry up. I have to take a shower.

223
00:16:16,646 --> 00:16:19,604
Give me some sandalwood.
I need to massage it on my head.

224
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,062
-Go.
-I'm going to take a shower.

225
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:24,521
Dhaani, tell me something.
Where is Neetu's wife?

226
00:16:24,604 --> 00:16:26,437
She never comes to family occasions.

227
00:16:26,521 --> 00:16:28,521
But it's her father-in-law's funeral.

228
00:16:28,604 --> 00:16:31,562
We'll ask Neetu whether
she's going to come or no.

229
00:16:31,646 --> 00:16:34,229
Everyone is in mourning.
She is no different, right?

230
00:16:34,312 --> 00:16:35,812
What will she do at home alone?

231
00:16:35,896 --> 00:16:37,937
-Anyway, go and put the mattresses out.
-Sure.

232
00:16:38,021 --> 00:16:42,562
I asked Saksham to play the piano.
He used to love listening to it.

233
00:16:43,354 --> 00:16:46,229
Then, I said it was late
and that he should sleep.

234
00:16:47,104 --> 00:16:49,562
-Then, I went to the kitchen.
-Auntie, are you okay?

235
00:16:49,646 --> 00:16:52,354
Saksham was about to leave…

236
00:16:53,146 --> 00:16:55,396
when he collapsed on the piano.

237
00:16:55,479 --> 00:16:56,437
Oh, no!

238
00:16:57,729 --> 00:17:00,062
I panicked, and I called Saksham.

239
00:17:00,354 --> 00:17:03,437
I asked him to check what happened to him.

240
00:17:03,521 --> 00:17:05,646
He came running, and then…

241
00:17:05,729 --> 00:17:09,187
When your own family isn't around,
the outsiders come to your rescue.

242
00:17:09,521 --> 00:17:11,396
True. Neighbors help you in these times.

243
00:17:13,479 --> 00:17:16,062
Sister… don't lose heart.

244
00:17:16,229 --> 00:17:17,687
Be brave, it'll be alright.

245
00:17:17,771 --> 00:17:19,354
I'll make us some tea.

246
00:17:20,229 --> 00:17:23,646
-Sorry, we're troubling you.
-No, not at all. Actually--

247
00:17:23,729 --> 00:17:25,271
-Yes.
-Move the pillow.

248
00:17:25,812 --> 00:17:27,771
I've asked them to get
some rotis, as well.

249
00:17:27,854 --> 00:17:29,104
I'll get it right away.

250
00:17:30,229 --> 00:17:31,771
She's feeling quite cold today.

251
00:17:31,854 --> 00:17:34,604
Look, she's wearing a sweater
as well as a shawl.

252
00:17:35,062 --> 00:17:37,354
I borrowed them from Mother-in-law
as soon as I got here.

253
00:17:37,437 --> 00:17:40,229
-Oh!
-Father-in-law had given it to her…

254
00:17:40,312 --> 00:17:41,771
-Really?
-on her birthday.

255
00:17:42,354 --> 00:17:43,229
Wow!

256
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:45,896
He had great taste.

257
00:17:46,104 --> 00:17:49,646
He'd given me a lovely pink sari
on Diwali this year.

258
00:17:49,979 --> 00:17:54,271
He said, "You should wear bright colors.
They suit you."

259
00:17:55,104 --> 00:17:57,771
He was the only one,
who used to get us gifts.

260
00:17:58,396 --> 00:18:00,771
He knew our likes and dislikes.

261
00:18:00,937 --> 00:18:02,812
He took care of us all.

262
00:18:03,687 --> 00:18:05,896
He must've been very
romantic in his time.

263
00:18:05,979 --> 00:18:07,771
Shut up. You're so cheeky.

264
00:18:08,646 --> 00:18:11,604
How do you think he fathered
an army of six children?

265
00:18:23,146 --> 00:18:23,979
Neetu.

266
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,229
Everyone's asleep.

267
00:18:26,979 --> 00:18:29,604
Oh… sorry.

268
00:18:30,187 --> 00:18:32,187
-All good?
-Yes.

269
00:18:42,396 --> 00:18:44,104
Mom, go and lie down.

270
00:18:44,646 --> 00:18:45,896
Yes. Go to sleep.

271
00:18:46,521 --> 00:18:51,604
I'm not feeling sleepy.
If I feel sleepy, I'll lie down here.

272
00:18:52,729 --> 00:18:54,854
Brother has already fallen asleep.

273
00:18:56,146 --> 00:18:59,021
-You should go upstairs and sleep. Go.
-All right.

274
00:18:59,437 --> 00:19:01,354
-Gajraj, sit here for a while.
-Okay.

275
00:19:02,729 --> 00:19:04,562
Don't worry. We'll manage.

276
00:19:05,646 --> 00:19:07,271
Mom, let me massage your feet.

277
00:19:09,604 --> 00:19:10,604
Come on.

278
00:19:15,687 --> 00:19:19,396
He really missed you. All of you.

279
00:19:20,437 --> 00:19:24,312
We wanted to visit you more often,
but how could we? Work kept us busy.

280
00:19:24,729 --> 00:19:25,562
Yes, Mom.

281
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:29,646
It's not like we didn't miss you and Dad.

282
00:19:31,187 --> 00:19:34,812
Pratibha always talked about
what a nice person he was.

283
00:19:35,062 --> 00:19:36,687
He had a very good heart…

284
00:19:37,312 --> 00:19:39,771
but he was an extremely finicky eater.

285
00:19:39,854 --> 00:19:42,396
No matter what you cook,
he'd always find faults in it.

286
00:19:42,479 --> 00:19:46,146
What are you saying, Pratibha?
He always ate whatever I served him.

287
00:19:46,479 --> 00:19:50,312
I used to argue with Mother-in-law,
but never with Father-in-law.

288
00:19:50,812 --> 00:19:52,437
Do you know what he used to say to me?

289
00:19:52,521 --> 00:19:55,312
He used to say,
"You're from an affluent family…

290
00:19:55,396 --> 00:19:57,687
so there's a style in everything you do."

291
00:19:58,312 --> 00:19:59,854
He rarely stayed with us.

292
00:20:00,187 --> 00:20:02,437
Later, my husband got so busy
with his work in Ayodhya.

293
00:20:02,729 --> 00:20:03,979
-Yeah, right.
-Oh, really?

294
00:20:04,396 --> 00:20:06,479
I thought you got fed up
with Mother-in-law's nagging.

295
00:20:06,562 --> 00:20:07,604
I'll hit you!

296
00:20:07,937 --> 00:20:11,937
I always wanted to stay here…
but Rahul had important exams then.

297
00:20:12,646 --> 00:20:14,896
How's our brother-in-law, Gajraj?

298
00:20:15,396 --> 00:20:17,187
Does he still drink himself to sleep?

299
00:20:17,271 --> 00:20:19,604
No. He stopped drinking ages ago.

300
00:20:20,104 --> 00:20:21,437
He still drinks.

301
00:20:21,854 --> 00:20:23,437
-Listen, sister-in-law!
-Yes?

302
00:20:25,021 --> 00:20:26,812
-Is our youngest sister-in-law…
-Yes?

303
00:20:27,312 --> 00:20:28,396
coming?

304
00:20:28,687 --> 00:20:30,104
-Where is she?
-I have no idea.

305
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,354
Was our late father-in-law
not up to her standards?

306
00:20:33,396 --> 00:20:34,687
You two are nasty!

307
00:20:35,229 --> 00:20:36,646
Be quiet.

308
00:20:36,896 --> 00:20:40,396
Let's go out, or else, the daughters
of this house will bawl us out.

309
00:20:40,479 --> 00:20:42,979
Yes, let's go. They're very dangerous.

310
00:20:43,062 --> 00:20:44,562
-Sister, take the blanket.
-Let's go.

311
00:20:44,646 --> 00:20:47,062
Everything else is fine, right?

312
00:20:47,229 --> 00:20:48,354
Want a drink, Mom?

313
00:20:48,937 --> 00:20:51,354
-Hey… I meant tea.
-All right.

314
00:20:52,021 --> 00:20:55,104
-Do you want tea? We'll get it.
-We can't make it here.

315
00:20:55,187 --> 00:20:56,229
Why not?

316
00:20:56,979 --> 00:20:59,396
-Why can't we have tea? It's so cold.
-Yes, we want some.

317
00:20:59,479 --> 00:21:01,604
We can have tea.
I'll ask Aunt Sheila to make it.

318
00:21:01,687 --> 00:21:03,687
-Why trouble her?
-Why should we bother her?

319
00:21:04,021 --> 00:21:05,437
Mom, can we make it here?

320
00:21:06,187 --> 00:21:08,062
You're not supposed to cook
when in mourning…

321
00:21:09,562 --> 00:21:11,104
but okay, go ahead.

322
00:21:11,187 --> 00:21:13,562
-All right.
-If you're making it, I'll also have some.

323
00:21:13,646 --> 00:21:16,854
-Let me make it then.
-Please, sit down.

324
00:21:16,937 --> 00:21:18,146
Who wants tea?

325
00:21:18,312 --> 00:21:19,562
-Me.
-Me.

326
00:21:19,646 --> 00:21:21,271
Make it for everyone, sister-in-law.

327
00:21:21,562 --> 00:21:23,562
-Add some jaggery to it.
-Yes.

328
00:21:24,062 --> 00:21:28,146
Remember how Dad used to love
having tea with jaggery?

329
00:21:28,687 --> 00:21:30,979
If you're making it with jaggery,
I'll also have some.

330
00:21:31,187 --> 00:21:33,021
Serve it in a steel glass.

331
00:21:33,854 --> 00:21:35,812
Can you get me my cough syrup?

332
00:21:35,896 --> 00:21:37,604
-Let's go.
-Where are you all going?

333
00:21:37,687 --> 00:21:40,271
You're going to make tea,
not to exchange chitchat.

334
00:21:40,396 --> 00:21:43,437
-Sushma!
-No, stay here. I'll make it.

335
00:21:43,521 --> 00:21:46,896
-Yes, Mom?
-Use the vessel kept on the top shelf.

336
00:21:47,479 --> 00:21:49,646
The cups are in the cupboard.

337
00:21:50,396 --> 00:21:51,437
Be careful.

338
00:21:52,229 --> 00:21:53,937
Okay, Mom. Will you have tea?

339
00:21:55,354 --> 00:21:57,104
Yes.

340
00:21:57,521 --> 00:22:01,604
-I'll be right back, sister-in-law.
-Go and get the cups.

341
00:22:02,437 --> 00:22:04,312
When did you last see Dad?

342
00:22:04,396 --> 00:22:07,562
Recently. We had come here
with the kids for Diwali.

343
00:22:07,937 --> 00:22:08,896
Tell him, Mom.

344
00:22:09,396 --> 00:22:11,521
I had planned to come, but I couldn't.

345
00:22:12,437 --> 00:22:14,354
I had not come here since last year.

346
00:22:14,854 --> 00:22:16,979
I thought we'd celebrate
the New Year's together.

347
00:22:17,729 --> 00:22:19,771
That's what happened.
We just kept thinking…

348
00:22:20,479 --> 00:22:22,312
while Mom was alone here.

349
00:22:22,521 --> 00:22:26,062
She had got used to doing everything
on her own since we got married.

350
00:22:26,687 --> 00:22:31,479
None of you came and stayed
here for a long time.

351
00:22:32,687 --> 00:22:36,521
Sister, our kids have schools…
and we have jobs.

352
00:22:36,604 --> 00:22:40,021
I know that, Pankaj, but don't your
kids ever get any holidays?

353
00:22:40,104 --> 00:22:42,687
And what about Neetu?
He doesn't even have kids.

354
00:22:42,771 --> 00:22:44,854
-Come on, sister!
-The interrogation's begun.

355
00:22:44,979 --> 00:22:46,437
I know, we were wrong.

356
00:22:46,521 --> 00:22:47,604
There it goes.

357
00:22:47,687 --> 00:22:49,437
-Such a pain in the neck!
-What's with the blackout now?

358
00:22:49,521 --> 00:22:50,812
-Who's this?
-Hey, what happened?

359
00:22:50,896 --> 00:22:52,646
-Go to sleep, child.
-Careful, sister.

360
00:22:52,729 --> 00:22:57,896
-Somebody, hold her hand.
-Dear, go and get a candle or a torch.

361
00:23:03,896 --> 00:23:06,437
Brother, did you find our wire?

362
00:23:06,937 --> 00:23:09,062
No, sir. All the wires
have been jumbled up.

363
00:23:09,604 --> 00:23:12,396
Auntie, can you get the poha ready?
I'll come back and cook it.

364
00:23:12,479 --> 00:23:13,396
All right.

365
00:23:13,896 --> 00:23:15,771
Do you want me to peel any
other vegetables than potatoes?

366
00:23:15,854 --> 00:23:18,104
Anything will do.
I'm just making poha.

367
00:23:18,354 --> 00:23:20,521
Sister-in-law, give Sister Rani a towel.

368
00:23:20,604 --> 00:23:21,937
Sure.

369
00:23:22,021 --> 00:23:23,521
Also, can you please wake up the kids?

370
00:23:23,604 --> 00:23:26,021
-All right.
-They need to take a shower. It's late.

371
00:23:26,104 --> 00:23:29,896
Sister, please put the mattresses out
to dry! They're smelling really bad!

372
00:23:29,979 --> 00:23:31,104
I'll do it right away.

373
00:23:31,187 --> 00:23:32,229
-Give it to me.
-Okay.

374
00:23:32,312 --> 00:23:35,396
-Listen! What shall we make for breakfast?
-I'm making poha.

375
00:23:35,479 --> 00:23:36,354
Okay.

376
00:23:36,521 --> 00:23:39,937
I end up doing all the housework here.

377
00:23:40,937 --> 00:23:42,562
-Did you take a shower?
-Yes.

378
00:23:42,646 --> 00:23:43,479
All right.

379
00:23:43,562 --> 00:23:45,604
I'm going to wake up
your useless brothers.

380
00:23:46,229 --> 00:23:47,562
Good morning, Uncle.

381
00:23:49,396 --> 00:23:51,562
What is this, dear?
You're still making tea.

382
00:23:51,646 --> 00:23:52,479
Have some, Uncle.

383
00:23:52,562 --> 00:23:54,271
It's already so late.
No, I don't want it.

384
00:23:55,521 --> 00:23:56,521
I'll have it.

385
00:23:56,979 --> 00:23:57,854
Put it back!

386
00:23:58,187 --> 00:23:59,521
Your brother-in-law
wants to take a shower.

387
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:00,646
-Give me the towel.
-Here.

388
00:24:00,729 --> 00:24:02,146
-Has Gajraj woken up?
-Yes.

389
00:24:02,229 --> 00:24:03,812
He has to attend the prayer meeting.

390
00:24:03,896 --> 00:24:06,437
Panditji is on his way.
Gajraj must be ready before he gets here.

391
00:24:06,521 --> 00:24:08,646
I've given him tea. That's all I know.

392
00:24:08,771 --> 00:24:11,771
-Check if the others are ready!
-That's what I'm doing, sister!

393
00:24:12,646 --> 00:24:15,937
What are you guys doing here?
Sister is hollering downstairs.

394
00:24:16,021 --> 00:24:17,812
-Get ready, and go downstairs!
-We're going.

395
00:24:19,437 --> 00:24:20,562
Hey, Sister Rani!

396
00:24:21,229 --> 00:24:23,104
I can't go to the toilet without this.

397
00:24:23,437 --> 00:24:26,479
Even if you have to go,
there's a long queue for it.

398
00:24:27,229 --> 00:24:30,312
This family is full of jokers.

399
00:24:31,396 --> 00:24:32,396
That's true.

400
00:24:32,687 --> 00:24:34,229
Who's taking so long to come out?

401
00:24:34,437 --> 00:24:37,021
Who else could it be!
Our uncle, who sits inside for an hour.

402
00:24:37,521 --> 00:24:40,062
-Oh.
-I hope he controls himself.

403
00:24:45,604 --> 00:24:46,729
How long are you staying?

404
00:24:47,771 --> 00:24:48,812
I don't know.

405
00:24:49,396 --> 00:24:50,771
What's the plan? I mean…

406
00:24:52,062 --> 00:24:53,396
are you staying until the 13th-day ritual

407
00:24:53,479 --> 00:24:55,021
or just until the fourth-day ritual?

408
00:24:56,354 --> 00:24:59,646
I don't know what the elders have decided.

409
00:25:01,021 --> 00:25:04,771
Anyway, I've told my colleagues
that my stay might get extended.

410
00:25:06,521 --> 00:25:07,771
But I may have to leave soon.

411
00:25:12,604 --> 00:25:13,646
Isn't Seema coming?

412
00:25:13,729 --> 00:25:14,687
Is that all right?

413
00:25:17,187 --> 00:25:18,062
You know her, right?

414
00:25:19,562 --> 00:25:20,771
What did you tell the family?

415
00:25:21,396 --> 00:25:22,687
I said that she's unwell…

416
00:25:23,104 --> 00:25:24,896
and that she'll come when she gets better.

417
00:25:25,812 --> 00:25:27,229
Good morning, Dad.

418
00:25:28,062 --> 00:25:29,396
Mom will understand,

419
00:25:30,396 --> 00:25:33,437
but sister makes a scene about everything.

420
00:25:33,771 --> 00:25:35,021
She's doing it already.

421
00:25:35,396 --> 00:25:36,979
-Come out.
-Kick the door open!

422
00:25:37,062 --> 00:25:39,771
-Wait, he'll come out!
-Has he fainted in there?

423
00:25:40,396 --> 00:25:41,437
Come out!

424
00:25:43,229 --> 00:25:44,354
Go!

425
00:25:45,896 --> 00:25:47,812
-Hurry up!
-Wait a minute.

426
00:25:48,646 --> 00:25:50,062
-You're always late.
-What?

427
00:25:51,062 --> 00:25:53,021
Must you lag behind
everyone wherever you go?

428
00:25:53,979 --> 00:25:56,604
Hey, brother! Brother!

429
00:25:57,229 --> 00:25:58,229
Help me wash my hands!

430
00:25:59,562 --> 00:26:00,979
Go on, help him.

431
00:26:03,479 --> 00:26:05,646
-Hold it down!
-I can't.

432
00:26:05,729 --> 00:26:07,354
You're so weird.

433
00:26:07,562 --> 00:26:08,604
-Uncle!
-Yes?

434
00:26:08,687 --> 00:26:10,521
Are you constipated?

435
00:26:10,604 --> 00:26:13,646
Yes. I ate something that
didn't suit my stomach.

436
00:26:13,729 --> 00:26:16,354
You should've told me.
I would have given you a tablet.

437
00:26:16,437 --> 00:26:18,479
I wanted it to go out
of my body naturally.

438
00:26:19,021 --> 00:26:20,979
May he rest in peace.

439
00:26:26,396 --> 00:26:28,062
-Look.
-Brother Manoj is here.

440
00:26:28,479 --> 00:26:29,687
Check this out.

441
00:26:30,521 --> 00:26:32,104
-Good.
-It's lovely.

442
00:26:32,604 --> 00:26:34,104
-Namaste.
-Be careful.

443
00:26:34,187 --> 00:26:36,437
It brings out my brother's personality.

444
00:26:37,146 --> 00:26:38,354
Good.

445
00:26:40,187 --> 00:26:41,104
Be careful.

446
00:26:57,187 --> 00:26:58,437
Mom, Panditji was saying…

447
00:26:59,687 --> 00:27:02,271
that he'll perform the ritual tomorrow.

448
00:27:06,396 --> 00:27:09,396
We have to decide whether we want
a 13-day ritual…

449
00:27:10,437 --> 00:27:12,104
or a four-day ritual.

450
00:27:13,937 --> 00:27:18,271
My brother is dead
and you want to shortcut the ritual?

451
00:27:20,062 --> 00:27:22,312
Brother,
Mom wants a 13-day ritual.

452
00:27:25,687 --> 00:27:26,729
All right.

453
00:27:28,146 --> 00:27:29,312
Let's do what she wants.

454
00:27:31,854 --> 00:27:32,687
Ask him.

455
00:27:32,771 --> 00:27:33,812
-Uncle…
-Yes, dear?

456
00:27:33,896 --> 00:27:36,062
Manoj and I are going to Benaras
with Dad's ashes.

457
00:27:36,146 --> 00:27:36,979
-Okay.
-Yeah.

458
00:27:37,062 --> 00:27:39,937
-No, Gajraj. You cannot go anywhere.
-Why not?

459
00:27:40,187 --> 00:27:41,729
You shaved your head for the ritual.

460
00:27:42,021 --> 00:27:44,479
So, you cannot leave the house.

461
00:27:44,937 --> 00:27:46,229
-Why not?
-Because--

462
00:27:46,896 --> 00:27:49,479
-If he wants to go, he can go.
-What are you saying!

463
00:27:49,562 --> 00:27:52,062
What? Is he supposed to help
the women with peeling the peas?

464
00:27:52,187 --> 00:27:54,854
Peas? You had said we
should eat simple food.

465
00:27:54,937 --> 00:27:56,104
-No--
-No, he doesn't mean that.

466
00:27:56,187 --> 00:27:57,312
Don't get confused.

467
00:27:58,562 --> 00:28:02,771
-You should all go. Enjoy the ride.
-Enjoy?

468
00:28:02,896 --> 00:28:04,562
Is this some carnival?

469
00:28:04,771 --> 00:28:08,271
-Everything's upside down in this house.
-You guys are impossible!

470
00:28:08,354 --> 00:28:09,271
I agree.

471
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:11,979
Uncle, you're like a third umpire.

472
00:28:12,062 --> 00:28:14,187
You tell us to eat simple food,
and then, you say something else.

473
00:28:14,271 --> 00:28:16,104
-Then, you ask us all to go out.
-Listen--

474
00:28:16,187 --> 00:28:19,187
We're talking about going out,
not about eating.

475
00:28:19,271 --> 00:28:20,187
Let's go.

476
00:28:21,396 --> 00:28:23,729
-Take my car.
-Yes, take our car.

477
00:28:23,979 --> 00:28:24,854
But--

478
00:28:25,937 --> 00:28:27,646
We'll get a taxi. It's okay.

479
00:28:27,729 --> 00:28:29,687
Why? Vinod is telling us to take his car.

480
00:28:29,771 --> 00:28:31,854
It's not Vinod's car. It's my car.

481
00:28:31,937 --> 00:28:33,437
-Right.
-Vinod's just the driver.

482
00:28:34,396 --> 00:28:36,146
Okay, then. You can drive from now onward.

483
00:28:36,229 --> 00:28:37,229
Hey, are you crazy?

484
00:28:37,521 --> 00:28:40,229
He just means that you drive the car,
so he's calling you the driver.

485
00:28:40,312 --> 00:28:42,896
-Sit down.
-I was thinking I should also come.

486
00:28:43,312 --> 00:28:46,604
-Uncle, can all four of us go?
-Yes, why not!

487
00:28:46,771 --> 00:28:49,187
After all, we're a family. Take the car.

488
00:28:49,271 --> 00:28:52,187
He said we can't eat green vegetables.
And now, he wants peas.

489
00:28:52,271 --> 00:28:55,562
-Let it go.
-We were talking about the car, brother.

490
00:28:55,646 --> 00:28:57,271
-About the car?
-Yes.

491
00:28:58,062 --> 00:29:01,521
Boys… have you just woken up?

492
00:29:02,229 --> 00:29:05,146
You're young.
Don't you go for a run in the morning?

493
00:29:06,396 --> 00:29:08,229
Are we here to mourn or to run?

494
00:29:08,396 --> 00:29:10,437
If you're here to mourn,
you should wake up early.

495
00:29:10,521 --> 00:29:12,979
Grandpa, we slept late.
That's why we couldn't wake up early.

496
00:29:13,604 --> 00:29:15,479
I didn't sleep the whole
night, yet I am awake.

497
00:29:15,562 --> 00:29:17,229
Why didn't you sleep, Uncle?

498
00:29:17,812 --> 00:29:23,021
-Prakash's snoring kept me awake.
-What?

499
00:29:23,437 --> 00:29:25,937
Mom, can we cook today at home?

500
00:29:26,396 --> 00:29:31,604
Well, the daughters-in-law can't
cook today… but you daughters can.

501
00:29:32,021 --> 00:29:34,229
-Namaste, sister.
-Namaste, Uncle.

502
00:29:34,312 --> 00:29:35,562
Namaste, Uncle.

503
00:29:37,062 --> 00:29:38,229
Go and take a shower!

504
00:29:38,687 --> 00:29:41,187
-Will you have some tea?
-No, we just had some.

505
00:29:43,437 --> 00:29:45,271
-How did it happen, sister?
-Keep quiet!

506
00:29:45,687 --> 00:29:46,646
Hear the story.

507
00:29:47,187 --> 00:29:50,521
He had his dinner.

508
00:29:51,021 --> 00:29:53,896
Then, he asked Saksham
to play the piano.

509
00:29:54,562 --> 00:29:56,896
He was listening to the music.

510
00:29:57,396 --> 00:30:00,104
Then, I said, "It's late, go to sleep."

511
00:30:00,187 --> 00:30:03,646
-Then, he--
-Mom, who is going to do the dishes?

512
00:30:05,562 --> 00:30:08,562
-Munni will do it.
-Okay. She'll also make the khichdi then.

513
00:30:08,937 --> 00:30:11,771
-Then--
-We'll need extra quilts and mattresses.

514
00:30:13,604 --> 00:30:14,979
Hire them from the tent vendor.

515
00:30:16,271 --> 00:30:17,979
Do you have his number?

516
00:30:19,021 --> 00:30:20,854
It's in the diary.

517
00:30:22,479 --> 00:30:28,104
Ask Aunt Sheila.
She'll give you his number. Go.

518
00:30:31,104 --> 00:30:34,354
Go to Aunt Sheila's house,
and ask her for the tent vendor's number.

519
00:30:34,437 --> 00:30:36,562
Munni? In a tent?

520
00:30:36,812 --> 00:30:38,687
You're shameless!

521
00:30:38,937 --> 00:30:42,604
-Just do what she said!
-Go, get the number. Be quick.

522
00:30:42,896 --> 00:30:44,646
-Brother--
-He collapsed on the piano.

523
00:30:46,396 --> 00:30:48,729
Who is it? Come in.

524
00:30:48,854 --> 00:30:49,896
Namaste, Auntie.

525
00:30:50,312 --> 00:30:51,646
-Who is it?
-I'm Samay.

526
00:30:51,729 --> 00:30:52,687
-And I'm Rahul.
-Yes.

527
00:30:53,479 --> 00:30:55,771
Oh… come! Sit down!

528
00:30:57,729 --> 00:30:59,521
I didn't recognize you.
You're all grown up.

529
00:31:00,312 --> 00:31:01,229
Bittu!

530
00:31:02,187 --> 00:31:04,479
-Bittu, come here!
-Yes, Mom?

531
00:31:05,229 --> 00:31:06,146
Look who's here.

532
00:31:07,312 --> 00:31:08,521
-Hi.
-Hi.

533
00:31:08,854 --> 00:31:10,312
Get them something to eat.

534
00:31:10,646 --> 00:31:14,062
What will you have? Tea or a cold drink?

535
00:31:14,146 --> 00:31:17,312
No, we're not staying. We need Munni's
number. It gets very cold at night.

536
00:31:17,854 --> 00:31:20,896
He wants the tent vendor's number
so that he can do the dishes.

537
00:31:22,021 --> 00:31:23,271
What are you saying?

538
00:31:23,562 --> 00:31:26,229
You mean, you need Munni's number
so she can do the dishes.

539
00:31:26,312 --> 00:31:28,729
And the vendor's number to hire
quilts and mattresses, right?

540
00:31:28,854 --> 00:31:30,479
-Right.
-That's what we said.

541
00:31:30,562 --> 00:31:34,396
Oh, okay. Don't worry.
Bittu will go with you.

542
00:31:35,729 --> 00:31:37,479
Sure, I'll come with you.

543
00:31:37,562 --> 00:31:39,896
There's no need. We'll go on our own.

544
00:31:40,312 --> 00:31:42,729
If it's nearby, we all can go.

545
00:31:42,979 --> 00:31:44,979
We've come here after so long,
we might not remember the way.

546
00:31:45,062 --> 00:31:46,896
Bittu will go with you.

547
00:31:48,312 --> 00:31:50,312
Here we are!

548
00:31:52,396 --> 00:31:55,354
Auntie Munni, come to the music
teacher's house from tomorrow.

549
00:31:55,437 --> 00:31:56,354
Mom has called you.

550
00:32:01,271 --> 00:32:04,062
Brother, come to the music
teacher's house tomorrow.

551
00:32:04,604 --> 00:32:05,646
Isn't he dead?

552
00:32:05,979 --> 00:32:08,312
That's why we're calling you.
Don't forget.

553
00:32:08,396 --> 00:32:09,229
All right.

554
00:32:09,479 --> 00:32:11,146
Where are we going now?

555
00:32:11,229 --> 00:32:13,729
-I'll drop you off at home.
-Let's ride around Lucknow.

556
00:32:13,812 --> 00:32:15,604
No, everyone must be waiting.

557
00:32:15,687 --> 00:32:17,979
Oh, shut up. We'll go home eventually.

558
00:32:18,312 --> 00:32:20,562
Let's go for a spin before that.

559
00:32:20,979 --> 00:32:23,687
-Is that a problem for you, Bittu?
-Let's go.

560
00:32:23,771 --> 00:32:26,354
-You'll get us thrashed.
-Stop worrying!

561
00:32:26,437 --> 00:32:31,187
A faraway wind makes my heart soar

562
00:32:31,271 --> 00:32:36,021
Why do I like the words you speak?

563
00:32:36,937 --> 00:32:39,937
Why does everything feel different?

564
00:32:40,021 --> 00:32:41,562
We don't know.

565
00:32:41,854 --> 00:32:43,979
-We don't see it that often.
-This is our uncle.

566
00:32:45,979 --> 00:32:46,896
Where were you?

567
00:32:47,354 --> 00:32:48,854
-We had gone to see Munni.
-What?

568
00:32:48,937 --> 00:32:50,479
I meant, we had gone to see the vendor.

569
00:32:50,562 --> 00:32:53,062
You're going to get
thrashed very badly, got it?

570
00:32:53,521 --> 00:32:56,312
-Why?
-I'll tell you before I thrash you.

571
00:32:56,646 --> 00:32:58,854
Get lost! Wash your face!

572
00:32:58,937 --> 00:33:01,146
Go on, get lost!
Send your uncle here!

573
00:33:02,771 --> 00:33:05,146
Here they are! Why are you so late?

574
00:33:05,229 --> 00:33:08,187
Just look at you!
Were you swimming in the dust?

575
00:33:08,271 --> 00:33:09,771
You'd only sent us to the tent vendor.

576
00:33:09,854 --> 00:33:12,271
-Yes, but you're late!
-So what?

577
00:33:12,354 --> 00:33:13,271
He's so insolent!

578
00:33:13,521 --> 00:33:14,687
It's getting late. Hurry up.

579
00:33:14,771 --> 00:33:16,729
The indicator's not working.
Put your hand out.

580
00:33:16,812 --> 00:33:19,437
I've been driving this car
since before you were born.

581
00:33:19,521 --> 00:33:20,396
Let's go!

582
00:33:20,479 --> 00:33:22,396
Make sure you do everything properly.

583
00:33:23,854 --> 00:33:25,479
-Hey, Brother Pankaj…
-Why don't you go?

584
00:33:25,562 --> 00:33:27,562
everyone's waiting for you in the car!

585
00:33:27,937 --> 00:33:30,187
-Yes, I'm coming. Wait for me.
-Let's go.

586
00:33:31,187 --> 00:33:32,604
How should I get in?

587
00:33:51,479 --> 00:33:52,479
-Right there.
-All right.

588
00:33:56,396 --> 00:33:57,729
-Where are you going?
-Brother!

589
00:33:57,979 --> 00:34:00,437
Let's go. Are you planning
to stay here tonight?

590
00:34:01,104 --> 00:34:03,104
I taught you how to drive.

591
00:34:04,979 --> 00:34:06,896
-Don't you know how to drive?
-Sorry, brother.

592
00:34:18,687 --> 00:34:20,604
Yes?

593
00:34:22,187 --> 00:34:25,104
So, when will you get here?

594
00:34:25,896 --> 00:34:28,187
Okay. I'll let them know.

595
00:34:28,396 --> 00:34:29,437
What happened?

596
00:34:29,562 --> 00:34:33,104
The car broke down. They won't be
back before tomorrow afternoon.

597
00:34:33,187 --> 00:34:36,062
-Oh, no!
-What a nuisance!

598
00:34:36,146 --> 00:34:39,187
I knew this would happen.
That car's a wreck.

599
00:34:39,479 --> 00:34:42,479
Where will they stay tonight? Now,
we have one more thing to worry about.

600
00:34:43,854 --> 00:34:44,687
Brother…

601
00:34:44,771 --> 00:34:48,604
you started smoking when
you were young, right?

602
00:34:48,812 --> 00:34:52,146
Yes! I remember I was very young…

603
00:34:52,312 --> 00:34:56,437
and when I first saw him smoke,
I got scared.

604
00:34:56,687 --> 00:34:59,104
-Oh.
-I thought, his mouth was on fire.

605
00:35:01,937 --> 00:35:04,771
-He's got thrashed many times.
-Yes.

606
00:35:05,021 --> 00:35:06,187
How, brother?

607
00:35:07,021 --> 00:35:11,437
Nothing. I was just puffing away…

608
00:35:12,104 --> 00:35:15,187
when someone came from behind
and said, "Give me a light."

609
00:35:15,271 --> 00:35:16,771
I turned back, and it was Dad.

610
00:35:17,104 --> 00:35:18,979
I got whacked on the spot.

611
00:35:19,062 --> 00:35:21,187
No, I'm not talking about that story.

612
00:35:22,521 --> 00:35:24,896
Once, he had talked back to Dad.

613
00:35:25,521 --> 00:35:28,187
He said, "Why are you scolding me?

614
00:35:28,729 --> 00:35:31,312
I've seen you and Mom sleeping naked."

615
00:35:33,729 --> 00:35:35,687
Say what you want, but I'm the eldest.

616
00:35:36,062 --> 00:35:38,187
-Of course!
-You're all like my children.

617
00:35:38,604 --> 00:35:42,521
I've seen Mom and Dad very closely.

618
00:35:42,854 --> 00:35:45,521
Often, I have seen them naked.

619
00:35:45,812 --> 00:35:50,062
-Not once, several times!
-Brother, let's call it a night.

620
00:35:50,187 --> 00:35:53,021
No matter how much our father--

621
00:35:53,229 --> 00:35:55,187
Don't make such a racket!
The others are sleeping.

622
00:35:55,271 --> 00:35:56,937
-Yes.
-Sorry, brother.

623
00:35:57,021 --> 00:35:57,937
Sorry.

624
00:35:59,021 --> 00:36:02,062
-Speak softly.
-Dad was a great man…

625
00:36:02,521 --> 00:36:04,646
but what did he do for us?

626
00:36:05,354 --> 00:36:09,104
Nothing. Music was all he cared about.

627
00:36:09,396 --> 00:36:11,104
And our mother…

628
00:36:11,896 --> 00:36:15,146
she's a very cunning lady.

629
00:36:16,146 --> 00:36:19,729
She turned our dad against me
and had me thrashed.

630
00:36:19,896 --> 00:36:22,479
-Enough, brother.
-Neetu, let him speak.

631
00:36:23,521 --> 00:36:26,812
A man shouldn't keep things bottled up.
It causes heartache.

632
00:36:27,229 --> 00:36:29,437
We're talking so openly
to each other for the first time.

633
00:36:29,687 --> 00:36:30,562
Look at me.

634
00:36:31,521 --> 00:36:33,604
Brother Gajraj,
whatever I've tried to do until now…

635
00:36:34,146 --> 00:36:35,562
has always failed miserably.

636
00:36:35,854 --> 00:36:37,687
-Pour me another.
-Look at me.

637
00:36:38,479 --> 00:36:40,146
It's been tough for me to make ends meet,

638
00:36:40,396 --> 00:36:42,729
but have any of you…

639
00:36:44,937 --> 00:36:49,312
ever asked me, "Manoj,
are you able to manage everything?"

640
00:36:50,729 --> 00:36:53,354
When I was born,
I was considered the lucky one.

641
00:36:53,437 --> 00:36:55,062
Remember, you used to say…

642
00:36:55,771 --> 00:36:59,146
"His birth has brought us luck.
We own a shop now.

643
00:36:59,229 --> 00:37:00,937
He's lucky, he's very lucky."

644
00:37:02,854 --> 00:37:04,312
The shop…

645
00:37:05,729 --> 00:37:08,021
Dad said that shop was his dream.

646
00:37:08,104 --> 00:37:11,437
My shop's the real deal.
My in-laws helped me run it.

647
00:37:11,646 --> 00:37:16,396
I respect them because they respect me.

648
00:37:16,479 --> 00:37:18,771
My in-laws are useless.

649
00:37:19,062 --> 00:37:21,437
No, our parents were useless. Right?

650
00:37:21,979 --> 00:37:24,729
They kept complaining
that we never visit them.

651
00:37:25,229 --> 00:37:27,979
But tell me something, did they
ever step foot outside their home?

652
00:37:28,062 --> 00:37:30,146
Neetu, you're doing fine.

653
00:37:31,146 --> 00:37:34,104
You're the youngest.
You're everyone's favorite.

654
00:37:34,937 --> 00:37:37,521
You always do whatever you want.

655
00:37:37,937 --> 00:37:40,312
-Maybe.
-Your wife listens to you.

656
00:37:40,396 --> 00:37:41,979
You even have dimples.

657
00:37:43,187 --> 00:37:44,146
And you…

658
00:37:48,229 --> 00:37:50,229
you used to sing really well, dear.

659
00:37:50,687 --> 00:37:54,354
-Why did you stop singing?
-Right. You're the best singer in Lucknow.

660
00:37:54,437 --> 00:37:56,771
-Yes!
-Sing us a song.

661
00:37:57,229 --> 00:38:01,437
-No, brother--
-Go on, sing for us. We rarely meet.

662
00:38:02,187 --> 00:38:03,187
I've stopped singing.

663
00:38:03,271 --> 00:38:05,687
Sing us a song, or else, I'll do it.

664
00:38:08,604 --> 00:38:11,312
What was the song that Dad used to sing?

665
00:38:11,687 --> 00:38:14,646
"I will take you around the world."

666
00:38:14,729 --> 00:38:16,146
-Yes.
-What was its tune?

667
00:38:17,229 --> 00:38:18,104
I know.

668
00:38:19,521 --> 00:38:21,396
He used to count to four.

669
00:38:21,896 --> 00:38:23,562
Yes, I remember.

670
00:38:31,771 --> 00:38:35,146
There's an unfinished task

671
00:38:35,604 --> 00:38:39,312
That I want you to finish

672
00:38:39,396 --> 00:38:45,354
Today, I'll explain to you
What life is all about

673
00:38:46,604 --> 00:38:50,646
It's a beautiful, deep secret

674
00:38:51,021 --> 00:38:54,021
I'll tell you all about it

675
00:38:54,896 --> 00:38:58,312
Do you see that village far ahead?

676
00:38:58,812 --> 00:39:02,271
Today, I'll give you a tour of it

677
00:39:07,896 --> 00:39:12,021
The darkness of the night

678
00:39:12,354 --> 00:39:14,896
Descends on time

679
00:39:15,937 --> 00:39:19,854
What you hold in your hand

680
00:39:20,104 --> 00:39:23,312
Is all you'll take with you

681
00:39:23,396 --> 00:39:25,646
On days like these

682
00:39:25,937 --> 00:39:30,396
I will teach you how to walk

683
00:39:31,312 --> 00:39:35,146
There's an unfinished task

684
00:39:35,562 --> 00:39:38,562
That I want you to finish

685
00:39:39,479 --> 00:39:42,979
I will make you sit by my side

686
00:39:43,062 --> 00:39:46,437
And explain the tune to you

687
00:39:46,521 --> 00:39:47,854
-All together!
-All together!

688
00:40:10,312 --> 00:40:12,312
It's like a drop of water

689
00:40:12,396 --> 00:40:17,521
Granny used to say
"Let me hear you sing!"

690
00:40:18,104 --> 00:40:21,687
Tell me the story

691
00:40:21,771 --> 00:40:24,937
Of the king and the queen again

692
00:40:29,812 --> 00:40:32,812
Let me hear it again

693
00:40:37,396 --> 00:40:39,396
Grandpa used to say

694
00:40:39,479 --> 00:40:44,562
"Take me for a ride
On the rocking horse!"

695
00:40:44,646 --> 00:40:48,771
Do you see that village far ahead?

696
00:40:49,187 --> 00:40:52,062
Give us a tour of it today

697
00:40:52,729 --> 00:40:56,479
Tell us the story

698
00:40:56,562 --> 00:41:00,437
Again today

699
00:41:16,271 --> 00:41:19,896
Give me those blue marbles

700
00:41:20,396 --> 00:41:23,437
Of memories again

701
00:41:24,479 --> 00:41:28,479
Let me fly that kite

702
00:41:28,646 --> 00:41:31,521
Of my childhood again

703
00:41:32,771 --> 00:41:36,104
Make me finish the unfinished task

704
00:41:36,812 --> 00:41:39,854
That you wanted me to finish

705
00:41:40,937 --> 00:41:44,604
Make us finish the unfinished task

706
00:41:44,937 --> 00:41:48,979
That you wanted us to finish

707
00:42:11,187 --> 00:42:12,937
I have diabetes. I don't want tea.

708
00:42:14,396 --> 00:42:15,521
Namaste.

709
00:42:16,896 --> 00:42:18,396
-Namaste.
-Namaste.

710
00:42:19,187 --> 00:42:20,312
That's my uncle and aunt.

711
00:42:22,146 --> 00:42:23,146
Sister…

712
00:42:23,271 --> 00:42:25,187
I hope she doesn't ask,
"How did it happen?"

713
00:42:25,854 --> 00:42:26,729
…how did it happen?

714
00:42:30,104 --> 00:42:35,312
He had his dinner.
Then, he asked Saksham to play the piano.

715
00:42:35,396 --> 00:42:36,937
You'll get us killed.

716
00:42:39,437 --> 00:42:40,854
Hey, what happened?

717
00:42:41,104 --> 00:42:42,812
You guys are shameless!

718
00:42:43,021 --> 00:42:44,604
I'm not making fun of anyone.

719
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:47,812
Poor Grandma repeats
the same thing again and again.

720
00:42:48,021 --> 00:42:49,271
What choice does she have?

721
00:42:49,437 --> 00:42:51,979
Everyone who comes here
asks her the same question.

722
00:42:52,104 --> 00:42:54,937
What else can they ask
in these circumstances?

723
00:42:55,021 --> 00:42:58,771
We should print a leaflet with
details of how Grandpa died.

724
00:42:58,937 --> 00:43:01,271
"This is what happened,
this is how it happened."

725
00:43:01,479 --> 00:43:03,312
Sister Paakhi, today is Sunday.

726
00:43:03,396 --> 00:43:05,812
There comes a cartoon film on
TV on Sunday. Can we watch it?

727
00:43:05,896 --> 00:43:08,104
No, we can't put on the TV in this house.

728
00:43:08,187 --> 00:43:11,937
But we can watch it in
the neighbor's house.

729
00:43:12,021 --> 00:43:14,604
-At Bittu's.
-Oh, really?

730
00:43:14,687 --> 00:43:18,146
The kids won't be able to enjoy it alone.
So, we should also go with them.

731
00:43:18,271 --> 00:43:20,812
-Right! Let's go!
-Get permission from the elders first.

732
00:43:20,896 --> 00:43:22,812
Forget them! They'll say no.

733
00:43:23,021 --> 00:43:24,687
-Let's go.
-They'll make a scene.

734
00:43:24,896 --> 00:43:28,104
You're going to get in trouble, anyway.
Aren't you supposed to go to the airport?

735
00:43:28,187 --> 00:43:30,104
Instead of doing that,
you're busy in chitchat!

736
00:43:30,187 --> 00:43:31,062
You're doomed!

737
00:43:31,146 --> 00:43:33,104
-Oh, no!
-Aunt Seema is coming! Let's go!

738
00:43:33,187 --> 00:43:34,396
Let's go quickly.

739
00:43:36,312 --> 00:43:38,687
-Hey, watch where you're going!
-Oh, sorry!

740
00:43:38,771 --> 00:43:40,271
-Such insolent boys!
-Hey, let's go!

741
00:43:41,104 --> 00:43:42,854
Hey, please don't mind. They're just kids.

742
00:43:44,812 --> 00:43:47,771
Tell Nishant not to worry.

743
00:43:48,146 --> 00:43:51,479
It's okay even if his in-laws don't come.

744
00:43:51,562 --> 00:43:53,979
-Everyone else is here.
-All right.

745
00:43:54,687 --> 00:43:57,687
-Why aren't they coming?
-They're big shots.

746
00:43:57,979 --> 00:43:59,479
Bigger than me?

747
00:43:59,604 --> 00:44:02,521
-Not agewise, Auntie. Statuswise.
-Are they so educated?

748
00:44:02,771 --> 00:44:05,479
Auntie, listen to the devotional song.

749
00:44:06,021 --> 00:44:08,854
-Pankaj, Neetu, come over here.
-Yes.

750
00:44:09,687 --> 00:44:10,687
Wait a minute.

751
00:44:10,979 --> 00:44:13,521
Panditji! We're supposed to write
just five letters, right?

752
00:44:13,604 --> 00:44:16,396
-Yes.
-No one writes letters anymore.

753
00:44:16,521 --> 00:44:18,062
It's the era of SMS.

754
00:44:18,146 --> 00:44:20,437
Even if it's an SMS,
you have to type it.

755
00:44:20,521 --> 00:44:21,521
Read its content.

756
00:44:21,729 --> 00:44:23,896
Brother-in-law, come forward.

757
00:44:24,062 --> 00:44:26,271
-Help us compose the message.
-I'm all ears. Go on.

758
00:44:26,354 --> 00:44:28,354
Hey, come on! Help them!

759
00:44:28,437 --> 00:44:29,812
-Brother Manoj, read it out.
-Yes.

760
00:44:31,396 --> 00:44:34,479
"We deeply regret to inform
you that our father…

761
00:44:34,562 --> 00:44:38,854
Mr. Ramprasad Bhargava
passed away on 19th December.

762
00:44:39,187 --> 00:44:41,437
The final day of mourning
is on 1st January--"

763
00:44:41,521 --> 00:44:43,271
-What… 1st January?
-There he goes.

764
00:44:43,354 --> 00:44:46,729
-No one will come on 1st January.
-Why not?

765
00:44:47,312 --> 00:44:48,771
Brother Gajraj is right.

766
00:44:49,437 --> 00:44:52,312
-Let's keep it on 2nd January.
-What?

767
00:44:52,771 --> 00:44:55,979
-We can even keep it on 31st December.
-How can we do that?

768
00:44:56,312 --> 00:45:01,521
-That won't make it 13 days.
-Everyone parties on 31st December.

769
00:45:01,729 --> 00:45:04,604
We can't start others' new year
with the 13th-day ritual, right?

770
00:45:04,687 --> 00:45:07,604
Are we supposed to consider
their happiness or our grief?

771
00:45:07,812 --> 00:45:12,646
What's the problem?
Keep it on the tenth day.

772
00:45:12,812 --> 00:45:14,854
Those who love you will definitely come.

773
00:45:14,937 --> 00:45:17,771
-What!
-That's nonsense.

774
00:45:18,021 --> 00:45:19,896
According to you,
I always talk nonsense.

775
00:45:19,979 --> 00:45:21,812
-Yes--
-You think I'm a fool!

776
00:45:21,979 --> 00:45:27,396
When you were in school, you had revised
geography chapters for a history test.

777
00:45:27,771 --> 00:45:30,479
-You had messed up the entire test.
-What about you?

778
00:45:30,604 --> 00:45:33,312
For the home economics class,
she had to do some cooking.

779
00:45:33,687 --> 00:45:36,729
Instead of adding salt,
she added soda and ruined everything.

780
00:45:36,812 --> 00:45:38,229
It was delicious!

781
00:45:38,312 --> 00:45:42,396
-Come to the point.
-Wait. Leave the space for the date blank.

782
00:45:42,479 --> 00:45:45,812
-We'll decide later.
-Why later, Gajraj? Let's decide now.

783
00:45:45,896 --> 00:45:46,771
But sister--

784
00:45:47,146 --> 00:45:48,396
-Panditji.
-Tell him.

785
00:45:48,771 --> 00:45:51,062
-Make it 1st January.
-As you please.

786
00:45:51,146 --> 00:45:52,646
-It's settled.
-But--

787
00:45:52,896 --> 00:45:54,479
What do you mean?

788
00:45:54,771 --> 00:45:58,771
Think about it. Once the date is
fixed, it can't be changed.

789
00:45:59,021 --> 00:46:03,312
-Do as Manoj says. He's an elder.
-Have you lost it? I'm the eldest!

790
00:46:03,396 --> 00:46:06,354
Calm down. Why are you making a scene?

791
00:46:06,646 --> 00:46:09,729
Don't you know the sequence
of the alphabets? "M" comes after "G."

792
00:46:09,896 --> 00:46:13,896
Mr. Prakash… every family
follows its rituals.

793
00:46:14,979 --> 00:46:18,646
Mr. Ramprasad was a great believer in
tradition. He was your father-in-law.

794
00:46:18,854 --> 00:46:22,146
Is this how you discuss his rituals?

795
00:46:22,229 --> 00:46:26,187
What are we doing wrong, Uncle?
We're following the tradition.

796
00:46:26,687 --> 00:46:28,146
Is this the way to talk to me?

797
00:46:28,562 --> 00:46:32,062
Uncle is right.
Let's do it the way he's suggesting.

798
00:46:32,146 --> 00:46:34,562
-Don't do it my way!
-We will do it your way.

799
00:46:34,646 --> 00:46:38,146
You'll have to tolerate me
until my sister is alive!

800
00:46:38,229 --> 00:46:41,562
-We can part ways later!
-Uncle, come with me.

801
00:46:41,646 --> 00:46:43,437
No, listen to me…

802
00:46:43,521 --> 00:46:45,271
No one understands a thing here!

803
00:46:45,354 --> 00:46:46,396
Brother, listen to me!

804
00:46:46,479 --> 00:46:48,687
-What happened?
-Brother Gajraj!

805
00:46:49,271 --> 00:46:50,896
Aunt Seema is here!

806
00:46:51,104 --> 00:46:52,604
Uncle, Auntie has arrived!

807
00:46:53,646 --> 00:46:55,396
-Namaste, Auntie!
-Tear an end of the letter

808
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:56,396
before sending it.

809
00:46:56,521 --> 00:46:57,687
-Should I tear it?
-Yes.

810
00:46:57,771 --> 00:46:58,687
All right.

811
00:46:59,687 --> 00:47:00,687
Auntie, give it to me.

812
00:47:02,979 --> 00:47:04,021
She is an actress.

813
00:47:04,104 --> 00:47:06,687
Just tear the corners of the letters.

814
00:47:07,146 --> 00:47:10,396
-Mom, isn't she an actress?
-The corners… yes!

815
00:47:10,687 --> 00:47:12,979
Hi, Seema! Seema's here!

816
00:47:13,437 --> 00:47:15,437
-After that, just post them!
-Seema!

817
00:47:16,854 --> 00:47:18,479
-How are you, Seema?
-How are you?

818
00:47:18,562 --> 00:47:21,354
-I am so glad you came.
-Finally, you're here.

819
00:47:22,396 --> 00:47:23,854
Is she the youngest daughter-in-law?

820
00:47:23,937 --> 00:47:25,979
She's rude!
She didn't pay her respects!

821
00:47:26,479 --> 00:47:27,562
Never mind, Auntie.

822
00:48:01,479 --> 00:48:04,562
You mustn't stop until you learn
to play a musical instrument properly.

823
00:48:04,646 --> 00:48:06,687
You must respect it.

824
00:48:19,521 --> 00:48:20,437
Mom.

825
00:48:21,146 --> 00:48:22,896
What's wrong, Mom?

826
00:48:24,604 --> 00:48:25,687
Are you missing Dad?

827
00:48:29,604 --> 00:48:32,187
Everyone's sleeping.
Let's go to the courtyard and talk.

828
00:48:33,146 --> 00:48:34,729
Come.

829
00:48:35,854 --> 00:48:37,521
Mom, did anyone hurt you?

830
00:48:37,771 --> 00:48:40,979
They're all crazy.
Don't pay attention to them.

831
00:48:41,104 --> 00:48:43,104
What happened? Tell me.

832
00:48:46,104 --> 00:48:48,479
I don't understand, Dhaani.

833
00:48:51,646 --> 00:48:54,937
I wanted us all to live together.

834
00:48:55,896 --> 00:48:59,146
All my children, daughters-in-law,
and grandchildren.

835
00:49:01,146 --> 00:49:06,771
And now that we're together…
I am feeling so lonely.

836
00:49:06,896 --> 00:49:07,979
Mom…

837
00:49:12,771 --> 00:49:14,937
You're going to stay here
until the 13th day, right?

838
00:49:15,312 --> 00:49:18,187
Yes, Mom. We're going to be here.

839
00:49:19,729 --> 00:49:22,021
Whom are you going to stay with now?
Have you decided?

840
00:49:26,312 --> 00:49:29,104
Mom, you can't live here alone.

841
00:49:33,521 --> 00:49:35,146
Tell me something.

842
00:49:35,854 --> 00:49:39,271
Is everything okay
between Nishant and Seema?

843
00:49:39,354 --> 00:49:40,937
Speak softly. She's here.

844
00:49:42,687 --> 00:49:45,437
Is there any problem
between Nishant and Seema?

845
00:49:46,271 --> 00:49:47,354
Looks like it.

846
00:49:48,979 --> 00:49:50,104
She seems distant.

847
00:49:53,271 --> 00:49:56,271
She never got along with us.

848
00:49:56,521 --> 00:50:00,021
Never mind, Mom.
It has always been like that.

849
00:50:00,562 --> 00:50:03,604
She moved to Mumbai to become an actress.
Did she make it? No.

850
00:50:04,062 --> 00:50:06,646
Have you ever seen her on TV?
Or in a film? No.

851
00:50:06,812 --> 00:50:08,646
She lives off her brother's fame.

852
00:50:09,729 --> 00:50:11,729
Her brother's nice.

853
00:50:11,812 --> 00:50:14,021
Nice? He's an actor.

854
00:50:14,104 --> 00:50:16,312
He's good at pretending.

855
00:50:18,104 --> 00:50:20,104
Never mind.

856
00:50:22,437 --> 00:50:24,521
Let's go inside. It's getting cold.

857
00:50:25,437 --> 00:50:27,146
-Let's go.
-Come on.

858
00:50:28,479 --> 00:50:29,521
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

859
00:50:29,604 --> 00:50:33,687
-You go ahead. I'll go to the washroom.
-Careful.

860
00:50:34,187 --> 00:50:35,062
Careful.

861
00:50:36,062 --> 00:50:39,646
-Let's go down this way.
-Why this way?

862
00:50:39,812 --> 00:50:42,937
-Dad had fallen down these stairs twice.
-Yes, I remember.

863
00:50:45,271 --> 00:50:47,937
-Nothing had happened to him then.
-Watch your step, brother.

864
00:50:48,021 --> 00:50:51,604
-Careful!
-This long dhoti…

865
00:50:52,812 --> 00:50:54,354
Why are you getting down backward?

866
00:50:54,437 --> 00:50:57,354
This is how you go downstairs…

867
00:50:58,271 --> 00:51:03,312
-if you're wearing a dhoti.
-Careful.

868
00:51:03,396 --> 00:51:06,979
-Did you see how smoothly I came down?
-Yes, awesome!

869
00:51:09,271 --> 00:51:11,229
-Speak softly, you'll wake up Mom.
-Oh, right.

870
00:51:11,312 --> 00:51:13,187
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

871
00:51:14,896 --> 00:51:16,396
Hey, this way.

872
00:51:16,479 --> 00:51:20,812
-Where's Neetu? I didn't see him today.
-That's because Seema is here now.

873
00:51:20,937 --> 00:51:22,771
I see!

874
00:51:24,521 --> 00:51:27,437
-He must be busy.
-Speak softly, or else, Mom will wake up.

875
00:51:39,437 --> 00:51:41,854
-We won't tell anyone.
-Keep quiet. Everyone's asleep.

876
00:51:42,896 --> 00:51:44,562
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

877
00:52:23,562 --> 00:52:25,312
Sister, look. They match perfectly.

878
00:52:26,854 --> 00:52:28,521
Let's go inside.

879
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:31,521
-How is it?
-The ghee you've ordered is perfect.

880
00:52:31,687 --> 00:52:33,562
-After all, it's my choice.
-The laddoos smell delicious.

881
00:52:33,646 --> 00:52:35,687
The kachoris should
also be fried in ghee.

882
00:52:35,771 --> 00:52:37,354
-Right.
-What is it, Uncle?

883
00:52:37,479 --> 00:52:41,021
-Are the kachoris ready?
-Don't worry, they're frying them.

884
00:52:41,104 --> 00:52:43,396
No, I am not worrying.
Just add some pulses into them.

885
00:52:43,521 --> 00:52:45,479
Don't worry. You'll love it.

886
00:52:45,562 --> 00:52:47,062
Why are you discussing all this here?

887
00:52:47,271 --> 00:52:52,312
Is this a funeral or a wedding?
The food needs to be simple.

888
00:52:52,396 --> 00:52:53,604
Make it bland, then.

889
00:52:53,979 --> 00:52:58,271
-You twist everything I say.
-No, I know it's for the 13th-day ritual,

890
00:52:58,354 --> 00:53:00,812
but people must like it.
The food must be tasty.

891
00:53:01,687 --> 00:53:03,562
The rice is full of stones.

892
00:53:03,812 --> 00:53:05,521
Let me make the tea.

893
00:53:05,729 --> 00:53:07,146
The tea's ready.

894
00:53:07,521 --> 00:53:09,021
Make some for yourself if you want.

895
00:53:09,229 --> 00:53:12,062
I can't make tea without
milk the way you do.

896
00:53:12,812 --> 00:53:14,062
I'll make it later.

897
00:53:14,437 --> 00:53:15,646
Let me serve it.

898
00:53:18,521 --> 00:53:22,146
-Why is she so keen on helping today?
-There are guests, that's why.

899
00:53:22,229 --> 00:53:24,812
She wants to show off her talent.
She's an actress, after all.

900
00:53:24,896 --> 00:53:26,479
You're wicked.

901
00:53:27,104 --> 00:53:29,479
Sister-in-law,
can you please pass the water jug?

902
00:53:29,562 --> 00:53:32,146
-It must be there.
-I just filled it.

903
00:53:32,229 --> 00:53:33,271
Thank you.

904
00:53:36,479 --> 00:53:38,562
I wanted to talk to you about something.

905
00:53:40,521 --> 00:53:42,396
Mom was weeping last night.

906
00:53:43,646 --> 00:53:45,312
She must be missing Dad.

907
00:53:46,021 --> 00:53:49,854
Yes… she's the only one who misses him.
I think we don't miss him.

908
00:53:50,146 --> 00:53:53,062
What are you saying?
You're taking this the wrong way.

909
00:53:53,146 --> 00:53:56,562
-We were just laughing--
-No, that's okay.

910
00:53:56,687 --> 00:53:58,562
I'm talking about what I'm seeing
in this house.

911
00:53:58,646 --> 00:54:01,521
What do you mean?
Speak more clearly.

912
00:54:01,937 --> 00:54:06,521
The truth is that
Mom cannot live here alone.

913
00:54:07,062 --> 00:54:11,854
So, let's decide whether you'll stay here
or take her along with you.

914
00:54:13,812 --> 00:54:17,729
How can we decide that?

915
00:54:18,146 --> 00:54:21,104
Mom should tell us what she wants to do.

916
00:54:21,896 --> 00:54:23,771
Mom won't be able to do that.

917
00:54:25,187 --> 00:54:26,104
I'll be right back.

918
00:54:28,396 --> 00:54:32,646
How could she say that!
It's between Mom and her sons, right?

919
00:54:33,104 --> 00:54:34,521
Who are we to decide?

920
00:54:34,729 --> 00:54:37,062
You're right.
Who wants to open Pandora's box, anyway!

921
00:54:52,146 --> 00:54:54,521
Pandora's box has been opened!

922
00:54:56,271 --> 00:54:57,979
-It's gone.
-Hey, Auntie!

923
00:55:01,854 --> 00:55:03,062
Seema!

924
00:55:04,312 --> 00:55:05,312
Seema.

925
00:55:05,562 --> 00:55:07,729
-What happened?
-Nothing.

926
00:55:07,896 --> 00:55:10,229
Then, why did you walk away from there?

927
00:55:10,729 --> 00:55:12,562
-Did we say something wrong?
-No.

928
00:55:12,687 --> 00:55:13,771
Then, what happened?

929
00:55:14,979 --> 00:55:19,521
If you don't like me, be honest…
but don't make fun of me.

930
00:55:19,646 --> 00:55:24,521
-Who was making fun of you?
-Am I a child? Can't I tell?

931
00:55:24,771 --> 00:55:26,646
You're always gossiping about me!

932
00:55:26,729 --> 00:55:32,312
Are you crazy? We don't gossip about
you at all. Dhaani was scolding us.

933
00:55:32,396 --> 00:55:34,812
-That's why we kept quiet.
-Why are you lying?

934
00:55:35,271 --> 00:55:38,604
When I was serving tea, you were
smirking as though I am an outsider.

935
00:55:38,687 --> 00:55:39,521
Seema--

936
00:55:39,604 --> 00:55:43,479
I'm trying to fit in,
but no one really wants me to do that.

937
00:55:43,562 --> 00:55:45,187
Speak softly.

938
00:55:45,271 --> 00:55:48,396
Look! When Father-in-law was sick,
I told Nishant to send him some money.

939
00:55:48,479 --> 00:55:52,604
I thought you all have responsibilities,
so you won't be able to help.

940
00:55:52,729 --> 00:55:54,979
-Look, Seema--
-It was not that easy for us either…

941
00:55:55,354 --> 00:55:56,521
but we helped.

942
00:55:56,979 --> 00:55:58,937
Did anyone thank me for that?

943
00:55:59,271 --> 00:56:01,687
Look, this isn't the right
time for this talk.

944
00:56:01,771 --> 00:56:03,979
Whenever you need money,
you think of us.

945
00:56:04,187 --> 00:56:06,646
Hey, what are you saying?

946
00:56:07,229 --> 00:56:09,021
Who begged you for money?

947
00:56:09,104 --> 00:56:13,104
I agree, we once took 25,000 rupees
from you for Rahul's school admission…

948
00:56:13,312 --> 00:56:15,271
but we returned it!

949
00:56:15,354 --> 00:56:18,437
You returned it, but Brother Pankaj
swallowed 50,000 from us!

950
00:56:18,562 --> 00:56:20,479
I don't know about that!

951
00:56:20,771 --> 00:56:23,521
That's between you two.
We've cleared our debts.

952
00:56:23,604 --> 00:56:26,062
Yeah, right.

953
00:56:26,187 --> 00:56:29,021
Do as you please, but keep me out of it!

954
00:56:29,104 --> 00:56:30,771
I'm already worried.

955
00:56:31,062 --> 00:56:34,021
Go and take a shower, or do you want
to remain filthy like your father?

956
00:56:40,771 --> 00:56:44,187
Look, I've been facing some financial
difficulties for the past four years.

957
00:56:45,062 --> 00:56:48,146
So, I thought the rent from Dad's shop
might help.

958
00:56:48,729 --> 00:56:50,896
He always said I was lucky for the shop…

959
00:56:51,729 --> 00:56:53,604
but he got sick,
so I couldn't say anything.

960
00:56:53,937 --> 00:56:57,146
-Calm down.
-Why? Do you think I'm drunk?

961
00:56:57,229 --> 00:56:58,187
Yes, you are drunk.

962
00:56:58,271 --> 00:57:01,854
I'm not drunk, Brother Manoj.
I'm hurt. That's it.

963
00:57:03,937 --> 00:57:08,687
I've been humiliated in front of everyone
for mere 50,000 rupees.

964
00:57:09,062 --> 00:57:11,812
Brother Pankaj,
no one has humiliated you.

965
00:57:11,896 --> 00:57:14,229
I don't even know about all this.

966
00:57:15,062 --> 00:57:16,062
Sit down.

967
00:57:16,229 --> 00:57:18,479
-Let's call Seema, and ask her.
-Forget it.

968
00:57:18,562 --> 00:57:21,896
Speak softly.
They can hear you downstairs.

969
00:57:22,521 --> 00:57:25,271
People enjoy conflicts, anyway.

970
00:57:25,812 --> 00:57:27,604
Don't add fuel to the fire.

971
00:57:27,979 --> 00:57:29,271
Who's adding fuel to the fire?

972
00:57:29,562 --> 00:57:31,729
-Are you talking to me?
-Speak softly, brother.

973
00:57:32,396 --> 00:57:36,562
Tell me something…
who brought up this topic?

974
00:57:37,646 --> 00:57:38,521
Seema.

975
00:57:38,854 --> 00:57:40,354
She said it to my face.

976
00:57:41,021 --> 00:57:43,229
No one cares for anyone here.

977
00:57:45,979 --> 00:57:49,437
I didn't say a word because…

978
00:57:50,146 --> 00:57:51,937
I'm neither the youngest nor the eldest.

979
00:57:53,021 --> 00:57:56,521
I was born as a middle child, by mistake.

980
00:57:56,729 --> 00:57:57,562
Me, too.

981
00:57:57,687 --> 00:58:01,229
The eldest sibling gives advice…
while the youngest sibling gets pampered.

982
00:58:02,187 --> 00:58:04,646
What about me?
I'm just stuck in the middle.

983
00:58:06,479 --> 00:58:07,479
I am useless!

984
00:58:09,521 --> 00:58:12,396
-Why are you--
-They tease me saying that…

985
00:58:12,479 --> 00:58:15,604
I belong to my wife's family now.

986
00:58:15,687 --> 00:58:18,146
-Let him say it!
-Yes, I belong to my wife's family.

987
00:58:19,604 --> 00:58:20,687
Don't think like that.

988
00:58:21,396 --> 00:58:23,062
Keep it down.

989
00:58:29,271 --> 00:58:32,896
-Uncle, let's go downstairs.
-Let's go.

990
00:58:39,437 --> 00:58:41,104
We'll just clean this, and join you.

991
00:58:45,646 --> 00:58:47,021
Did he urinate here?

992
00:58:49,229 --> 00:58:51,146
-I'll clean it.
-Should I help you?

993
00:58:57,312 --> 00:58:59,812
Seema, can you serve the tea?

994
00:59:03,104 --> 00:59:03,979
Here.

995
00:59:04,562 --> 00:59:06,687
Who wants to handle her mood
swings, anyway!

996
00:59:07,646 --> 00:59:09,396
Forget it now, Seema!

997
00:59:09,771 --> 00:59:12,187
Just remember why you're here!

998
00:59:12,312 --> 00:59:14,354
We can sort the grievances later.

999
00:59:14,604 --> 00:59:16,104
We won't meet again anytime soon.

1000
00:59:16,604 --> 00:59:18,437
Mom is going to live a long life.

1001
00:59:23,479 --> 00:59:24,437
What did she say?

1002
00:59:24,521 --> 00:59:27,271
Keep quiet.
People get what they deserve.

1003
00:59:27,354 --> 00:59:29,187
Why talk like that about Mom?

1004
00:59:29,771 --> 00:59:31,479
Why? It's not like Mom's an angel.

1005
00:59:31,896 --> 00:59:34,937
She cursed Dad all her life.
Then, why is she grieving now?

1006
00:59:35,021 --> 00:59:38,271
-Don't say that.
-Don't we fight with our husbands?

1007
00:59:38,354 --> 00:59:39,646
What are you saying?

1008
00:59:40,437 --> 00:59:42,104
Of course, you'll defend Mom.

1009
00:59:42,979 --> 00:59:45,896
You always got what you wanted, after all.

1010
00:59:45,979 --> 00:59:48,187
-Sister--
-Everyone turned a blind eye toward me.

1011
00:59:48,271 --> 00:59:49,896
It's not the time to discuss all this.

1012
00:59:49,979 --> 00:59:53,062
I was so young when it all happened.

1013
00:59:53,146 --> 00:59:55,812
-I don't even remember.
-Yeah, right. I grew up too soon.

1014
00:59:56,312 --> 01:00:00,604
I was 16 years old. I wasn't allowed
to study or train for any job.

1015
01:00:00,896 --> 01:00:02,896
They just married me off.

1016
01:00:03,187 --> 01:00:04,354
She's right.

1017
01:00:04,437 --> 01:00:07,729
Yes, but things were different then.

1018
01:00:07,854 --> 01:00:10,271
No one knew your husband
didn't have a steady job.

1019
01:00:10,354 --> 01:00:12,604
They knew. Mom knew everything.

1020
01:00:13,062 --> 01:00:16,437
She just wanted
to get rid of us, one by one.

1021
01:00:16,521 --> 01:00:19,812
Speak softly.
If Mom overhears us, how would she feel?

1022
01:00:20,937 --> 01:00:24,354
Whether you agree or not,
your husband loves you a lot.

1023
01:00:24,521 --> 01:00:25,729
Love, my foot!

1024
01:00:26,104 --> 01:00:29,104
He lied about his job, so obviously,
he'd pretend that he loves me.

1025
01:00:29,854 --> 01:00:33,479
I've always had to entreat my
parents to fulfill my wishes.

1026
01:00:33,562 --> 01:00:35,229
It's okay to ask for help from our family.

1027
01:00:35,312 --> 01:00:37,896
No, Pratibha!
I got an earful about it in return!

1028
01:00:38,104 --> 01:00:40,521
What was I supposed to do?
Whom should I have asked for help?

1029
01:00:41,896 --> 01:00:44,771
Tell me, has anyone ever respected
my husband in this house?

1030
01:00:44,854 --> 01:00:48,312
Whatever may be the occasion,
he's made to work the hardest.

1031
01:00:48,812 --> 01:00:52,479
But that didn't make any difference!
They still complained about him!

1032
01:00:52,562 --> 01:00:55,562
Sister, no one's complaining.
Don't say this.

1033
01:00:56,021 --> 01:00:58,062
Everyone respects him.

1034
01:00:58,146 --> 01:01:00,729
Forget it!
I see how everyone respects him!

1035
01:01:00,812 --> 01:01:03,229
Everyone's always in a bad mood.

1036
01:01:04,312 --> 01:01:05,437
Move!

1037
01:01:11,187 --> 01:01:13,146
She always enters at the right time.

1038
01:01:14,979 --> 01:01:15,812
Please, come.

1039
01:01:31,437 --> 01:01:34,854
Sister-in-law, this is Mr. Awasthi.
He works at your bank.

1040
01:01:38,896 --> 01:01:42,896
I was very sad to hear…
about your husband.

1041
01:01:44,229 --> 01:01:47,187
After all, no one can
interfere with God's will.

1042
01:01:48,271 --> 01:01:49,812
This isn't the right time…

1043
01:01:50,604 --> 01:01:54,479
but I have to say this. A few years ago,
your husband had taken a loan.

1044
01:01:55,312 --> 01:01:57,896
Initially, the monthly
installments were paid on time…

1045
01:01:57,979 --> 01:02:02,562
but then, they stopped.
The bank even served him a notice.

1046
01:02:03,104 --> 01:02:04,729
Now that the interest
rate is going to increase,

1047
01:02:04,812 --> 01:02:07,354
the repayments will also be higher.

1048
01:02:08,354 --> 01:02:12,229
There's enough money in
his account for this month.

1049
01:02:12,354 --> 01:02:17,396
You two have a joint account,
so I'll need your signature.

1050
01:02:17,604 --> 01:02:20,271
I don't understand all this.

1051
01:02:20,437 --> 01:02:24,771
-Can you please talk to my son, Manoj?
-Sure, I had met him once.

1052
01:02:27,146 --> 01:02:29,229
-What's the amount of the loan?
-Well--

1053
01:02:29,312 --> 01:02:31,812
Wait! Sir, let's talk outside.

1054
01:02:31,896 --> 01:02:34,687
Uncle, I also need
a loan for a motorcycle.

1055
01:02:34,771 --> 01:02:35,604
Shut up.

1056
01:02:36,187 --> 01:02:37,021
Please, come.

1057
01:02:37,312 --> 01:02:39,437
Brother Gajraj,
Dad took a loan of a million rupees!

1058
01:02:39,521 --> 01:02:41,979
He only returned three lakhs.
Seven lakhs are remaining.

1059
01:02:42,062 --> 01:02:43,521
-Eight, not seven.
-How?

1060
01:02:44,146 --> 01:02:45,354
The interest of a lakh rupees.

1061
01:02:45,646 --> 01:02:47,646
-Oh, no--
-He also mortgaged the shop.

1062
01:02:48,271 --> 01:02:50,771
-What are you saying?
-Yes, I'm telling the truth.

1063
01:02:52,771 --> 01:02:55,562
But what did he need this loan for?

1064
01:02:55,771 --> 01:02:59,437
We all must discuss this. Not just
us brothers, but our sisters as well.

1065
01:03:00,604 --> 01:03:02,646
He might have taken the loan for them.

1066
01:03:02,729 --> 01:03:05,896
I had also borrowed money from
him, but I returned it immediately.

1067
01:03:05,979 --> 01:03:09,354
Well, we all have borrowed
money from Dad at some point.

1068
01:03:09,437 --> 01:03:10,729
I haven't.

1069
01:03:10,812 --> 01:03:12,312
You have no responsibilities.

1070
01:03:12,729 --> 01:03:14,021
-Stop it!
-What?

1071
01:03:14,604 --> 01:03:17,271
As if you have heaps of responsibilities.

1072
01:03:17,354 --> 01:03:19,562
-Of course, I have responsibilities.
-You take money from your in-laws.

1073
01:03:19,646 --> 01:03:21,229
Responsibilities, my foot!

1074
01:03:21,396 --> 01:03:24,687
-I'll talk to Mom.
-Let's do it right now.

1075
01:03:24,771 --> 01:03:26,854
Now? She must be asleep.

1076
01:03:26,937 --> 01:03:28,979
Too many people visit us during the day.

1077
01:03:29,062 --> 01:03:31,646
On top of that, our uncle keeps
poking his nose in our business.

1078
01:03:34,854 --> 01:03:37,854
You rascal!
You're always picking on him.

1079
01:03:37,937 --> 01:03:43,271
-You've pampered him too much. Let's go.
-You're going too far.

1080
01:03:43,354 --> 01:03:44,187
Let's go.

1081
01:03:44,271 --> 01:03:48,187
-Where is he going now?
-Dad had fallen down these stairs twice.

1082
01:03:48,271 --> 01:03:50,187
-Let's go down from that side.
-Come.

1083
01:03:50,271 --> 01:03:51,396
Come. Walk straight.

1084
01:03:53,687 --> 01:03:54,604
What is it?

1085
01:03:54,687 --> 01:03:56,979
-Dhaani, is Mom asleep?
-Yes.

1086
01:03:57,396 --> 01:03:59,729
-Wake her up. We want to talk to her.
-She's asleep.

1087
01:03:59,812 --> 01:04:01,979
-Switch on the lights.
-Why are you--

1088
01:04:02,062 --> 01:04:03,229
What's happening?

1089
01:04:09,104 --> 01:04:09,979
Mom.

1090
01:04:11,104 --> 01:04:12,187
Sit down.

1091
01:04:13,104 --> 01:04:14,062
Sit down.

1092
01:04:17,646 --> 01:04:19,021
-Everyone's here.
-What's wrong?

1093
01:04:19,104 --> 01:04:21,229
-Nothing.
-What is it?

1094
01:04:24,271 --> 01:04:25,354
What happened?

1095
01:04:30,979 --> 01:04:31,896
Tell me.

1096
01:04:37,687 --> 01:04:43,687
Mom… we wanted to know why
Dad took such a big loan.

1097
01:04:46,104 --> 01:04:51,896
I mean… why did he need so much money?

1098
01:04:54,187 --> 01:04:56,437
Tell them, Mom, why he needed the money.

1099
01:04:58,896 --> 01:05:01,396
They'd never come to discuss
anything with you before today.

1100
01:05:01,937 --> 01:05:02,812
What!

1101
01:05:03,187 --> 01:05:06,312
Now that they found out about the loan,
they're all over you.

1102
01:05:06,562 --> 01:05:07,812
Go ahead, blame me.

1103
01:05:08,521 --> 01:05:10,812
I've always been
the needy one in this family.

1104
01:05:11,104 --> 01:05:13,312
-Sister, we're not talking about you.
-Why are you--

1105
01:05:13,396 --> 01:05:15,896
Are you talking about me then?

1106
01:05:15,979 --> 01:05:18,812
-Be quiet, Uncle's asleep.
-Don't start now.

1107
01:05:18,896 --> 01:05:21,896
Dhaani… get me Dad's diary.

1108
01:05:24,479 --> 01:05:25,729
-His diary?
-Yes.

1109
01:05:27,937 --> 01:05:29,562
Yes, that's the one.

1110
01:05:29,646 --> 01:05:30,854
What's in it, Mom?

1111
01:05:31,021 --> 01:05:31,979
Here.

1112
01:05:34,896 --> 01:05:36,312
Yes, that's Dad's diary.

1113
01:05:38,937 --> 01:05:40,646
Had he taken any more loans?

1114
01:05:42,021 --> 01:05:45,062
-He must have mentioned why he took it.
-What's written in there, brother?

1115
01:05:47,146 --> 01:05:49,646
FINAL TALLIES

1116
01:05:52,229 --> 01:05:53,646
The tallies.

1117
01:05:54,479 --> 01:05:56,354
-What?
-Read it.

1118
01:05:57,521 --> 01:06:02,562
"On 23rd June 2013,
I gave 125,000 to Manoj."

1119
01:06:02,812 --> 01:06:05,521
-Yes, but we'd returned it.
-We had returned it.

1120
01:06:05,604 --> 01:06:07,437
-You'd returned 75,000.
-Did you hear that?

1121
01:06:07,812 --> 01:06:08,646
Only 75,000?

1122
01:06:08,729 --> 01:06:12,854
"On 4th June 2013,
I gave 35,000 to Rani's husband."

1123
01:06:13,021 --> 01:06:15,979
We didn't even ask for it.
Mom forced it on us.

1124
01:06:16,062 --> 01:06:19,687
Sister, I'm just reading what's
written here. No one's blaming you.

1125
01:06:20,146 --> 01:06:24,687
"On 5th July 2013, I had given them
30,000. They haven't returned it."

1126
01:06:25,437 --> 01:06:29,146
"Once, I gave 20,000 to Gajraj.
He returned it."

1127
01:06:29,771 --> 01:06:32,146
-That's what he's written.
-We had returned all of it.

1128
01:06:32,229 --> 01:06:33,062
What about 50,000--

1129
01:06:33,146 --> 01:06:35,229
-"Pankaj took 75,000."
-We'd returned it.

1130
01:06:35,312 --> 01:06:38,771
"In 2013, 50,000.
In 2014, another 75,000."

1131
01:06:38,854 --> 01:06:40,271
But we had returned all of it.

1132
01:06:40,354 --> 01:06:42,521
-Oh, you returned it.
-How much did you return?

1133
01:06:42,604 --> 01:06:44,312
I guess, 30,000.

1134
01:06:44,396 --> 01:06:47,146
You've returned just 60,000.

1135
01:06:48,062 --> 01:06:49,854
You'd borrowed 25,000
for your brother-in-law's

1136
01:06:49,937 --> 01:06:51,479
-daughter's wedding.
-Mom, where are you going?

1137
01:06:51,562 --> 01:06:53,812
-Why would I do that?
-It's all written here.

1138
01:07:12,937 --> 01:07:14,521
Tell me if you need anything.

1139
01:07:14,604 --> 01:07:17,229
-What is all this?
-What's your problem?

1140
01:07:30,104 --> 01:07:34,937
Saksham was about
to leave, and right then…

1141
01:07:44,854 --> 01:07:48,687
he collapsed on the piano.

1142
01:07:49,646 --> 01:07:52,646
I called Saksham.
I was so scared.

1143
01:07:52,854 --> 01:07:55,812
I asked him to see what had happened.

1144
01:07:56,187 --> 01:07:59,687
He just left us.

1145
01:08:01,354 --> 01:08:03,937
Grandma, why are you crying?

1146
01:08:04,687 --> 01:08:06,854
Come here, dear.

1147
01:08:09,271 --> 01:08:11,354
-Please, have something.
-I don't want to eat!

1148
01:08:11,646 --> 01:08:14,521
I've been eating this bland
food for five days now!

1149
01:08:14,896 --> 01:08:17,604
-Here.
-It's tasteless! How can I eat it!

1150
01:08:17,687 --> 01:08:19,271
-Auntie, take this.
-I don't want to eat!

1151
01:08:19,354 --> 01:08:20,812
-Grandma…
-She doesn't want to eat.

1152
01:08:20,896 --> 01:08:23,687
put your dentures in.
I'll order a pizza for you.

1153
01:08:28,812 --> 01:08:29,729
Go to hell!

1154
01:08:35,146 --> 01:08:38,354
Even if we manage to save 100,000
each, it still won't be enough.

1155
01:08:39,646 --> 01:08:41,521
From where we're supposed
to get even 100,000?

1156
01:08:42,521 --> 01:08:44,479
We barely cover our monthly expenses.

1157
01:08:44,562 --> 01:08:47,729
How are you dividing the loan, brother?

1158
01:08:48,396 --> 01:08:50,437
Everyone must return what they owe.

1159
01:08:51,396 --> 01:08:55,437
What about the interest?
We need to pay that as well.

1160
01:08:57,604 --> 01:08:58,562
Okay, then.

1161
01:08:59,687 --> 01:09:00,646
Let's sell the shop.

1162
01:09:02,521 --> 01:09:04,479
Why are you after the shop?

1163
01:09:05,479 --> 01:09:08,187
Anyway, we can't sell it.
It's been mortgaged.

1164
01:09:09,312 --> 01:09:12,437
Brother, if we keep the shop, it'll
be of some use in such times of need.

1165
01:09:12,729 --> 01:09:16,229
You should've let me run it.
I would've made it work.

1166
01:09:16,437 --> 01:09:17,937
-Yes, but--
-You simply mortgaged it.

1167
01:09:18,354 --> 01:09:22,354
As if you could have made it work!

1168
01:09:22,687 --> 01:09:24,812
Let's sell the house, then.

1169
01:09:25,021 --> 01:09:25,979
The house?

1170
01:09:26,187 --> 01:09:27,604
-Which house? This one?
-Here's tea.

1171
01:09:28,437 --> 01:09:30,437
Put it down.

1172
01:09:31,896 --> 01:09:33,771
Why did you sit down?
You'd better go.

1173
01:09:33,854 --> 01:09:35,687
What will I do downstairs?

1174
01:09:35,937 --> 01:09:37,937
-They're quarreling.
-Who's quarreling?

1175
01:09:39,521 --> 01:09:42,396
Well… there's only one
conflict in this house.

1176
01:09:49,437 --> 01:09:51,062
-Okay.
-I'm better than you all.

1177
01:09:51,146 --> 01:09:53,729
You think I'm bad because
I cut ties with the family…

1178
01:09:53,979 --> 01:09:56,896
-but I didn't land the family in debt.
-Seema, keep quiet!

1179
01:09:57,479 --> 01:10:00,937
What's wrong with you? You're
always creating trouble! Enough now!

1180
01:10:01,937 --> 01:10:04,896
If you can't be polite,
then at least, stop fighting.

1181
01:10:04,979 --> 01:10:08,187
Brother Neetu, please go. We'll handle it.

1182
01:10:08,271 --> 01:10:10,437
-Don't get involved in their quarrels.
-Come on, go.

1183
01:10:10,521 --> 01:10:12,021
-It's late. You should sleep.
-Right.

1184
01:10:12,104 --> 01:10:13,229
Drop it.

1185
01:10:13,562 --> 01:10:14,562
Let's go.

1186
01:10:18,771 --> 01:10:21,021
Seema, don't make a scene.

1187
01:10:21,104 --> 01:10:24,479
There are guests here.
Don't shame the family.

1188
01:10:24,729 --> 01:10:27,062
We'll talk when they leave.

1189
01:10:27,146 --> 01:10:30,437
Why? Are you scared of the outsiders?
Tell me.

1190
01:10:30,896 --> 01:10:32,812
Carry on with your charade later.

1191
01:10:32,979 --> 01:10:35,354
Tell me, who's really bothered
about Dad's loan?

1192
01:10:35,521 --> 01:10:37,687
You're just worried about saving
your own money.

1193
01:10:38,437 --> 01:10:40,354
Don't even get me started.

1194
01:10:40,521 --> 01:10:43,146
I can say the same thing, Seema!

1195
01:10:43,229 --> 01:10:45,104
If I started talking, you'd be in trouble.

1196
01:10:45,604 --> 01:10:49,271
-What have I done?
-Drop it. Don't act so innocent.

1197
01:10:49,521 --> 01:10:52,479
As if you don't know what
happened to Brother Neetu.

1198
01:10:52,562 --> 01:10:56,312
Let it be. Everyone knows
why Brother Neetu had to get a job.

1199
01:10:56,479 --> 01:10:59,146
-He loves children so much, and you--
-Sister-in-law.

1200
01:10:59,354 --> 01:11:02,104
They'll have children soon.
They've only been married for six years.

1201
01:11:02,187 --> 01:11:04,812
-Exactly.
-He had to leave this house…

1202
01:11:04,896 --> 01:11:06,896
because she wanted to be an actress.

1203
01:11:06,979 --> 01:11:10,146
Look what happened to the most
loved son of this family.

1204
01:11:11,187 --> 01:11:13,312
Forget it.

1205
01:11:13,437 --> 01:11:17,146
Seema, I'd suggest you move
into the room upstairs.

1206
01:11:17,437 --> 01:11:18,479
It's for the best.

1207
01:11:27,729 --> 01:11:30,062
How is she going to manage alone?

1208
01:11:58,396 --> 01:12:00,062
What now?

1209
01:12:01,146 --> 01:12:02,729
I want to go back to Mumbai.

1210
01:12:04,854 --> 01:12:06,104
I looked for the tickets…

1211
01:12:07,479 --> 01:12:10,937
but all the flights are booked
because of New Year's Eve.

1212
01:12:12,646 --> 01:12:13,937
There's a flight on 2nd January.

1213
01:12:15,187 --> 01:12:18,104
If we stay here until then,
we'll be here for the 13th-day ritual.

1214
01:12:18,479 --> 01:12:20,437
I feel suffocated here, Nishant.

1215
01:12:25,937 --> 01:12:26,812
Want some?

1216
01:12:27,812 --> 01:12:28,729
No.

1217
01:12:32,479 --> 01:12:35,771
Seema… the situation
is quite tense right now.

1218
01:12:35,896 --> 01:12:37,396
Manage for a few more days, please.

1219
01:12:39,354 --> 01:12:41,687
If you want,
you can sleep in the room upstairs.

1220
01:12:43,146 --> 01:12:46,187
You don't need to come down.
I'll make them understand.

1221
01:12:46,271 --> 01:12:47,396
Will they understand?

1222
01:12:48,187 --> 01:12:51,646
Nishant, don't you think
we've tried enough to fit in?

1223
01:12:52,312 --> 01:12:53,187
But they're just--

1224
01:12:54,021 --> 01:12:57,146
They ask us for money when they need
it, and humiliate us otherwise.

1225
01:12:57,354 --> 01:12:59,187
-How is that okay?
-What choice do we have?

1226
01:12:59,771 --> 01:13:02,646
There's been a death in the family.
This is not the time to argue.

1227
01:13:02,729 --> 01:13:05,729
I'm not asking you to argue with them.
Just tell them to accept the truth.

1228
01:13:05,812 --> 01:13:08,562
Which truth, Seema?
Who accepts the truth?

1229
01:13:10,354 --> 01:13:11,729
You talk about others.

1230
01:13:12,187 --> 01:13:14,562
Do you have the guts
to accept your truth?

1231
01:13:15,479 --> 01:13:18,062
What truth are you talking about?

1232
01:13:18,604 --> 01:13:21,771
-You're also blaming me just like them!
-Drop it, Seema.

1233
01:13:22,604 --> 01:13:26,021
Pack your things.
I'll find you a hotel tomorrow.

1234
01:13:26,104 --> 01:13:28,979
Nishant, wait a minute. Just hear me out.

1235
01:14:00,104 --> 01:14:01,979
Auntie?

1236
01:14:06,021 --> 01:14:06,896
Auntie.

1237
01:14:08,729 --> 01:14:09,604
Hey!

1238
01:14:11,562 --> 01:14:12,937
Why are you crying?

1239
01:14:13,062 --> 01:14:16,021
It's nothing, Rahul. Don't talk to me.
I'm a bad person.

1240
01:14:16,271 --> 01:14:19,354
-Why are you talking like this-- Wait!
-I'm going.

1241
01:14:19,437 --> 01:14:21,562
-Where are you going?
-Mumbai.

1242
01:14:21,646 --> 01:14:23,604
Mumbai? Wait a minute, Auntie!

1243
01:14:23,687 --> 01:14:28,146
-No one likes me here.
-I do. Anyway, let me open it for you.

1244
01:14:32,687 --> 01:14:33,687
There.

1245
01:14:37,521 --> 01:14:39,229
So, you like me.

1246
01:14:42,562 --> 01:14:45,396
Yes… I like you.
You're my aunt, after all--

1247
01:14:45,479 --> 01:14:50,437
Not in that way.
You like me as in you "like me."

1248
01:14:50,729 --> 01:14:51,604
What?

1249
01:14:53,062 --> 01:14:56,104
-No?
-No. Why are you saying this?

1250
01:14:57,021 --> 01:15:00,104
Another lie. You're also lying.

1251
01:15:01,271 --> 01:15:04,604
If you like me, then say it!
Whom are you scared of?

1252
01:15:04,687 --> 01:15:07,354
-I'll talk to them.
-Auntie! Please, wait!

1253
01:15:11,062 --> 01:15:12,146
-Let go.
-Yes.

1254
01:15:18,854 --> 01:15:19,729
Sit down.

1255
01:15:23,062 --> 01:15:23,937
The thing is…

1256
01:15:26,062 --> 01:15:29,771
all your uncles and aunts…

1257
01:15:29,854 --> 01:15:32,687
keep lying to each other.

1258
01:15:34,229 --> 01:15:36,479
They don't like each other.

1259
01:15:36,979 --> 01:15:38,896
Your grandma doesn't like them either.

1260
01:15:39,354 --> 01:15:40,687
She dislikes me the most.

1261
01:15:42,271 --> 01:15:43,312
Never mind.

1262
01:15:47,562 --> 01:15:51,979
But they're our blood relatives,
so we must respect them. Right?

1263
01:15:53,812 --> 01:15:58,354
I was an outsider, who was expected
to please everyone in the family.

1264
01:15:58,896 --> 01:16:02,354
I couldn't do that,
so they labeled me as a "bad" person.

1265
01:16:10,562 --> 01:16:13,354
-Am I boring you?
-No.

1266
01:16:14,312 --> 01:16:16,771
No, why would you bore me!

1267
01:16:21,312 --> 01:16:22,646
Okay… you better go.

1268
01:16:24,312 --> 01:16:25,979
-It's very late.
-Yeah.

1269
01:16:26,979 --> 01:16:30,479
-Let me take this.
-Go, Rahul. You must sleep.

1270
01:16:30,562 --> 01:16:33,437
-Yes. You should also sleep.
-Yes.

1271
01:16:35,104 --> 01:16:38,771
-Okay, good night.
-Good night, Auntie.

1272
01:16:40,854 --> 01:16:42,729
-I'll lie down.
-Sure.

1273
01:16:47,687 --> 01:16:49,896
Don't tell anyone about this.

1274
01:16:50,271 --> 01:16:52,229
-No, I won't.
-Good.

1275
01:17:59,687 --> 01:18:00,604
Who is it?

1276
01:18:11,729 --> 01:18:14,562
Oh, no! Today's the 31st.
No one remembered.

1277
01:18:14,854 --> 01:18:16,854
-What?
-It's New Year's Eve.

1278
01:18:17,021 --> 01:18:18,896
As if we were celebrating it.

1279
01:18:18,979 --> 01:18:22,562
I'm not talking about that. We forgot
that it was Mom's birthday yesterday.

1280
01:18:22,646 --> 01:18:25,437
-Oh, yes!
-Oh, yes! I completely forgot!

1281
01:18:25,521 --> 01:18:28,937
You started your chitchat again!
You're always talking!

1282
01:18:29,229 --> 01:18:33,312
Sister Rani, we were just wondering…
how old is Mom?

1283
01:18:33,646 --> 01:18:34,854
Must be about 60 or 62.

1284
01:18:35,937 --> 01:18:38,229
-Her hair's still black. How is that?
-What?

1285
01:18:38,896 --> 01:18:41,104
So, Dad was younger than Mom!

1286
01:18:41,187 --> 01:18:42,396
Are you crazy?

1287
01:18:42,521 --> 01:18:45,312
If Dad was 60 years old,
then how could Mom be 62 years old?

1288
01:18:45,396 --> 01:18:48,146
Who told you that?
There was a gap of 12 years between them.

1289
01:18:48,229 --> 01:18:49,729
Then, how old is Mom?

1290
01:18:50,021 --> 01:18:52,812
I was born when she was 16 or 17.

1291
01:18:53,479 --> 01:18:55,146
You're 54 now.

1292
01:18:56,479 --> 01:18:57,937
I'm only 53.

1293
01:18:58,062 --> 01:19:02,021
-You're still very young, then!
-She's so insolent.

1294
01:19:18,771 --> 01:19:22,271
-What is it? Tell me!
-What happened to you, brother-in-law?

1295
01:19:27,271 --> 01:19:30,021
I didn't like the tea.

1296
01:19:30,104 --> 01:19:31,937
Oh, no. Here. Sister, have tea.

1297
01:19:35,062 --> 01:19:36,021
Shall we leave?

1298
01:19:37,521 --> 01:19:40,562
-How long are you going to sit here?
-How could I forget that she's my aunt?

1299
01:19:42,271 --> 01:19:43,396
How am I supposed to face her now?

1300
01:19:43,479 --> 01:19:47,312
Forget about it. I was the only one who
saw you. I doubt she'll tell anyone.

1301
01:19:47,646 --> 01:19:50,437
She has a bad character, I'm telling you.
I always knew it.

1302
01:19:52,354 --> 01:19:53,771
She is good at heart.

1303
01:19:54,521 --> 01:19:56,479
She's not like the other aunts.

1304
01:19:57,104 --> 01:19:59,187
-Do you mean my mother?
-That's not what I meant.

1305
01:19:59,271 --> 01:20:02,146
I mean, she's not the person
you think she is.

1306
01:20:04,437 --> 01:20:06,687
Seema is very pure.

1307
01:20:06,771 --> 01:20:09,687
Did you smoke hash this morning?

1308
01:20:11,187 --> 01:20:13,562
She's our aunt.
Don't think about falling for her.

1309
01:20:14,812 --> 01:20:18,479
Sometimes, I feel like hugging her
and showering her with love.

1310
01:20:18,562 --> 01:20:21,021
-Are you crazy--
-Whom do you want to hug?

1311
01:20:24,812 --> 01:20:25,687
This one.

1312
01:20:28,729 --> 01:20:30,396
What's going on?

1313
01:20:30,896 --> 01:20:32,687
Brother Samay, let's go home.

1314
01:20:33,146 --> 01:20:35,021
Let's leave the two lovebirds alone.

1315
01:20:35,271 --> 01:20:36,104
Let's go!

1316
01:20:36,187 --> 01:20:37,562
-Take your hands off me!
-You're looking beautiful.

1317
01:20:37,646 --> 01:20:40,479
-All right, calm down.
-Hey, why do you misunderstand me?

1318
01:20:40,562 --> 01:20:43,854
The tea is ready. You can have it.
Hope it doesn't get cold.

1319
01:20:43,937 --> 01:20:45,146
You are funny!

1320
01:20:45,562 --> 01:20:48,979
Seema, come! Will you have some tea?

1321
01:20:49,187 --> 01:20:52,604
-Sure, I'll make it.
-The tea is ready. Here you go.

1322
01:20:53,062 --> 01:20:56,479
Check if there's enough sugar.
We have added very little sugar to it.

1323
01:20:57,104 --> 01:21:00,812
Sister-in-law, can you please pass me
the biscuits? Auntie is feeling dizzy.

1324
01:21:00,896 --> 01:21:02,104
-What happened?
-Relax. Sit down.

1325
01:21:02,187 --> 01:21:05,021
-Be careful!
-Have a seat.

1326
01:21:05,646 --> 01:21:07,271
-Have some water.
-Yes. Give it to me.

1327
01:21:07,354 --> 01:21:09,271
You'll feel better in no time.

1328
01:21:09,437 --> 01:21:10,604
And what about--

1329
01:21:11,187 --> 01:21:13,271
Seema, you woke up late today.

1330
01:21:13,896 --> 01:21:15,854
Yes, I had a headache.

1331
01:21:15,937 --> 01:21:17,479
Take care of yourself.

1332
01:21:17,562 --> 01:21:21,604
It's so cold and your room
is on the terrace.

1333
01:21:21,687 --> 01:21:24,812
-Yes.
-Nishant slept downstairs with Mom.

1334
01:21:24,896 --> 01:21:27,479
-Oh, really?
-Check if the stove is vacant.

1335
01:21:27,604 --> 01:21:30,271
Make some ginger tea.

1336
01:21:30,354 --> 01:21:31,521
-Yes.
-Sure.

1337
01:21:32,771 --> 01:21:35,646
-I'll make it.
-Do you know how to make tea?

1338
01:21:35,937 --> 01:21:38,854
Auntie, Seema cooks really well.

1339
01:21:38,937 --> 01:21:42,312
Really? How would I know?
I've never tasted her food.

1340
01:21:42,646 --> 01:21:45,562
My husband's been unwell
since he got up today.

1341
01:21:45,646 --> 01:21:47,187
-What's wrong?
-The usual.

1342
01:21:48,271 --> 01:21:50,479
-Oh, you mean cold?
-Yeah, it's freezing outside.

1343
01:21:50,562 --> 01:21:51,396
Right.

1344
01:21:51,479 --> 01:21:54,812
Listen, add some black pepper to the tea.

1345
01:21:54,896 --> 01:21:58,896
-All right.
-And some cinnamon, as well.

1346
01:21:59,437 --> 01:22:02,271
Also, add a few tulsi leaves
and ginger powder.

1347
01:22:02,354 --> 01:22:07,229
-Should we also fry it with cumin?
-You're so cheeky.

1348
01:22:07,312 --> 01:22:09,437
Auntie, you carry on. I'll get the tea.

1349
01:22:09,937 --> 01:22:11,021
All right.

1350
01:22:11,104 --> 01:22:14,729
-Will you manage, or should I help?
-Be careful.

1351
01:22:17,271 --> 01:22:18,604
Are you staying, Seema?

1352
01:22:19,771 --> 01:22:20,646
Yes.

1353
01:22:21,854 --> 01:22:25,146
Good. Otherwise,
things would have gotten worse.

1354
01:22:26,896 --> 01:22:28,354
I hope you're not mad at me.

1355
01:22:29,729 --> 01:22:30,771
No, sister-in-law.

1356
01:22:33,354 --> 01:22:34,229
She's moody.

1357
01:22:38,437 --> 01:22:41,396
-Give me the newspaper.
-Yes, even I want to read it.

1358
01:22:42,396 --> 01:22:45,896
-Happy New Year!
-Happy New Year!

1359
01:22:48,437 --> 01:22:51,479
-There are always people around--
-Someone's here.

1360
01:22:55,271 --> 01:22:56,479
There's no one here.

1361
01:22:57,146 --> 01:22:58,437
Happy New Year, sister-in-law.

1362
01:23:07,771 --> 01:23:10,104
Come… sit down.

1363
01:23:13,146 --> 01:23:15,646
You're wearing Dad's jacket, right?

1364
01:23:16,562 --> 01:23:18,896
-Mom gave it to me.
-Yeah, right!

1365
01:23:19,312 --> 01:23:22,896
Everyone's already started
cleaning out stuff. So shameless.

1366
01:23:53,937 --> 01:23:57,146
Hey, what are you doing?

1367
01:23:58,062 --> 01:24:00,437
-Hey, wait!
-I'm leaving. Bye.

1368
01:24:00,521 --> 01:24:02,396
What's with these tantrums? Kiss me!

1369
01:24:04,687 --> 01:24:06,146
-What happened?
-Nothing.

1370
01:24:09,479 --> 01:24:11,687
Go away. Go!

1371
01:24:12,104 --> 01:24:13,104
I'll see you tomorrow.

1372
01:24:18,604 --> 01:24:19,646
Auntie!

1373
01:24:25,521 --> 01:24:26,812
Why aren't you sleeping?

1374
01:24:28,604 --> 01:24:31,021
Everyone's asleep, so I thought
you must be sleeping as well.

1375
01:24:36,646 --> 01:24:39,104
It's so cold out here.

1376
01:24:47,062 --> 01:24:50,104
They'll be dividing this house very soon.

1377
01:24:50,646 --> 01:24:51,604
You should sell it.

1378
01:24:52,479 --> 01:24:53,812
No one has offered to help you.

1379
01:24:54,229 --> 01:24:58,812
No. Actually,
Nishant had asked me to stay with him.

1380
01:24:59,729 --> 01:25:01,437
So, why don't you go with him?

1381
01:25:02,187 --> 01:25:03,687
How can I go with him, brother?

1382
01:25:04,687 --> 01:25:06,812
Seema's there with him.

1383
01:25:07,104 --> 01:25:09,062
Seema and sister-in-law never got along.

1384
01:25:10,021 --> 01:25:13,437
Then, take turns.
Stay wherever you feel happy.

1385
01:25:13,562 --> 01:25:16,146
Your other daughters-in-law are nice.

1386
01:25:17,021 --> 01:25:19,021
They're just show-offs, brother.

1387
01:25:20,812 --> 01:25:22,562
They're nice, but only from a distance.

1388
01:25:23,104 --> 01:25:29,062
You're right. Now, look at us.
Who bothers to come and see us?

1389
01:25:29,396 --> 01:25:31,896
They just call me
and say, "I love you, Mom!"

1390
01:25:31,979 --> 01:25:33,729
Don't go on about yourself!

1391
01:25:36,646 --> 01:25:38,729
Tell me. What will you do now?

1392
01:25:41,146 --> 01:25:42,021
I don't know.

1393
01:25:44,562 --> 01:25:47,729
I never imagined I'd be so alone.

1394
01:25:49,437 --> 01:25:52,312
It hasn't even been
13 days since he died…

1395
01:25:53,687 --> 01:25:55,479
and they're already squabbling.

1396
01:25:58,646 --> 01:26:00,312
Sometimes, it feels as though…

1397
01:26:02,687 --> 01:26:07,854
they're celebrating a marriage
or a happy occasion.

1398
01:26:09,771 --> 01:26:13,271
Just because you're offering flowers or…

1399
01:26:13,812 --> 01:26:18,354
lighting a lamp in front of his
picture doesn't mean you're grieving.

1400
01:26:20,354 --> 01:26:23,979
I'm not saying that they
should cry for 13 days…

1401
01:26:25,562 --> 01:26:29,437
but at least, they should
not forget why they're here.

1402
01:26:32,312 --> 01:26:34,062
They shouldn't forget whom they've lost.

1403
01:26:34,187 --> 01:26:38,396
I know what they've been doing.

1404
01:26:39,229 --> 01:26:41,104
They're constantly talking about things…

1405
01:26:41,354 --> 01:26:43,521
they've done for you and their father.

1406
01:26:43,896 --> 01:26:46,187
Do they have no shame?

1407
01:26:46,396 --> 01:26:50,687
Did you ever make a list of
the things you've done for them?

1408
01:26:52,687 --> 01:26:57,854
All his desires were crushed under
the burden of our responsibilities.

1409
01:26:59,771 --> 01:27:03,271
But he never complained to anyone.

1410
01:27:04,979 --> 01:27:07,896
He kept himself happy
by playing the piano.

1411
01:27:08,604 --> 01:27:09,562
He'd say…

1412
01:27:11,229 --> 01:27:14,854
"I could make these musical
instruments sound melodic,

1413
01:27:15,354 --> 01:27:20,937
but I couldn't bring harmony
in the lives of my children."

1414
01:27:23,562 --> 01:27:27,229
I never really understood
what he meant then.

1415
01:27:29,479 --> 01:27:31,354
I'm sorry I couldn't help you, Laali.

1416
01:27:33,979 --> 01:27:35,562
They're just ungrateful.

1417
01:27:37,062 --> 01:27:38,687
It's not their fault.

1418
01:27:42,312 --> 01:27:44,562
I guess our parenting was wrong.

1419
01:27:46,896 --> 01:27:50,854
We never taught them…
to be grateful for anything.

1420
01:27:52,354 --> 01:27:55,521
We always take our near
and dear ones for granted.

1421
01:27:55,937 --> 01:27:58,146
We never thank them…

1422
01:27:58,521 --> 01:28:02,021
or apologize to them.

1423
01:28:02,479 --> 01:28:07,312
We think it's their duty
to do things for us.

1424
01:28:08,146 --> 01:28:11,062
We forget that they are just helping us.

1425
01:28:18,354 --> 01:28:19,979
Would you please sign that?

1426
01:28:20,562 --> 01:28:21,937
You're having an abortion… why?

1427
01:28:22,354 --> 01:28:23,896
Because I want to.

1428
01:28:30,146 --> 01:28:32,937
We must thank them…

1429
01:28:34,771 --> 01:28:36,896
before it's too late.

1430
01:28:39,021 --> 01:28:42,604
How did your hand

1431
01:28:43,146 --> 01:28:46,312
Slip out of my hand?

1432
01:28:46,396 --> 01:28:47,437
Thank you.

1433
01:28:48,437 --> 01:28:52,396
You were never so unfeeling

1434
01:28:52,979 --> 01:28:56,354
Toward us

1435
01:29:18,979 --> 01:29:23,437
I have always yearned to pause

1436
01:29:23,979 --> 01:29:27,437
The time in my hands

1437
01:29:29,396 --> 01:29:33,521
Time that just slipped away

1438
01:29:34,021 --> 01:29:38,771
Never to be shackled

1439
01:29:38,854 --> 01:29:42,562
Take me in your arms today

1440
01:29:43,146 --> 01:29:47,729
So that I fall asleep

1441
01:29:49,104 --> 01:29:51,354
Without you by my side

1442
01:29:51,521 --> 01:29:56,104
My sleep has evaded me for many nights

1443
01:30:03,937 --> 01:30:04,896
Uncle!

1444
01:30:06,646 --> 01:30:09,771
I hope you'll come out today! Are you
planning to catch the train from in there?

1445
01:30:09,854 --> 01:30:12,229
Check once if he's got
down at the last station.

1446
01:30:12,396 --> 01:30:14,812
Just check. Oh, he's come out.

1447
01:30:15,771 --> 01:30:19,521
You're a pain in the neck! Should I
just flush myself down the toilet?

1448
01:30:20,271 --> 01:30:22,271
-Help me wash my hands.
-There's such a long queue.

1449
01:30:22,354 --> 01:30:24,646
-No one lets him take a dump in peace.
-Here's the towel!

1450
01:30:24,729 --> 01:30:26,604
-What are you doing--
-Take the towel.

1451
01:30:26,896 --> 01:30:28,521
-What about the bucket?
-Oh, right.

1452
01:30:28,604 --> 01:30:29,979
-Here it is.
-Hey…

1453
01:30:30,062 --> 01:30:31,229
-take it from him.
-Move aside!

1454
01:30:31,312 --> 01:30:32,646
-The water's hot.
-Step aside!

1455
01:30:32,729 --> 01:30:34,729
-Come on, take it.
-Move out of the way!

1456
01:30:35,104 --> 01:30:37,271
-Take the towel.
-Here, take it.

1457
01:30:37,937 --> 01:30:39,396
Take a shower out here now.

1458
01:30:40,146 --> 01:30:43,646
I've ironed your kurta.
Put it on after taking a shower.

1459
01:30:45,062 --> 01:30:46,021
Listen…

1460
01:30:49,021 --> 01:30:49,979
thank you.

1461
01:31:00,937 --> 01:31:03,396
-What are you doing?
-I'm taking a selfie.

1462
01:31:04,021 --> 01:31:05,104
Stupid!

1463
01:31:05,646 --> 01:31:07,729
Tell him it's not done!

1464
01:31:08,437 --> 01:31:09,854
What-- No!

1465
01:31:10,021 --> 01:31:11,312
Don't do that!

1466
01:31:11,896 --> 01:31:12,812
Don't!

1467
01:31:19,229 --> 01:31:20,771
What are you doing here? Come on.

1468
01:31:20,854 --> 01:31:23,187
-Don't you understand why you're here?
-Let's take a photo.

1469
01:31:24,479 --> 01:31:26,146
-We also want to join!
-Yes!

1470
01:31:28,896 --> 01:31:31,646
Auntie, can you move a little bit?
Yes, thank you.

1471
01:31:31,979 --> 01:31:32,854
Rahul.

1472
01:31:35,812 --> 01:31:36,729
Go!

1473
01:31:43,687 --> 01:31:46,396
Hey, can you please pass the sabzi?

1474
01:31:47,437 --> 01:31:48,729
We want some more.

1475
01:32:01,562 --> 01:32:03,312
Hey, have some more.

1476
01:32:03,396 --> 01:32:06,146
Yes, sure. Wait.

1477
01:32:12,562 --> 01:32:15,146
-You're looking nice.
-Thank you.

1478
01:32:48,604 --> 01:32:53,729
The people we thought of as our own

1479
01:32:56,771 --> 01:32:58,062
No more puris are left.

1480
01:32:58,146 --> 01:33:01,687
-Did the kids have their breakfast?
-Give them something.

1481
01:33:03,562 --> 01:33:09,562
To imagine we had to explain to them

1482
01:33:10,771 --> 01:33:15,062
The meaning of rituals

1483
01:33:21,687 --> 01:33:25,312
The roads, the alleys, and every corner

1484
01:33:25,562 --> 01:33:29,187
Of the house were left behind

1485
01:33:29,271 --> 01:33:34,979
Who could say that I once lived here?

1486
01:33:36,896 --> 01:33:39,979
The garland of breathes is now undone

1487
01:33:40,479 --> 01:33:43,687
How to weave it together again?

1488
01:33:44,104 --> 01:33:47,396
No one listens to the old songs

1489
01:33:47,854 --> 01:33:50,854
We once sang

1490
01:33:58,271 --> 01:34:00,937
-Are the rituals done? Is anything left?
-All done.

1491
01:34:01,021 --> 01:34:02,271
-Can we get up?
-Sure!

1492
01:34:02,354 --> 01:34:03,979
-Let's get up then.
-Let's have some food.

1493
01:34:04,062 --> 01:34:05,312
-Where's Uncle?
-Hey, watch out!

1494
01:34:05,396 --> 01:34:08,729
-Oh, no! Be careful!
-Brother!

1495
01:34:08,812 --> 01:34:12,062
-This means, Dad has left the house.
-What happened?

1496
01:34:12,562 --> 01:34:16,146
How could he just leave?
He hadn't even eaten yet.

1497
01:34:16,354 --> 01:34:19,729
The soul does not care for food.
It's free from all things.

1498
01:34:19,812 --> 01:34:24,604
-So, does the soul go away hungry?
-This ritual is for his salvation.

1499
01:34:24,937 --> 01:34:29,896
Laali, now,
it's our duty to release his soul.

1500
01:34:30,771 --> 01:34:34,312
So that when the soul is
freed, it can find peace.

1501
01:34:34,396 --> 01:34:35,604
-Right, Panditji?
-Yes.

1502
01:34:35,896 --> 01:34:38,687
After a year, you'll have to repeat
the same ritual.

1503
01:34:38,771 --> 01:34:40,562
-You'll have to come back.
-Everyone?

1504
01:34:40,646 --> 01:34:42,854
-Yes, everyone.
-But why everybody?

1505
01:34:43,354 --> 01:34:46,104
What if someone can't come back?

1506
01:34:46,646 --> 01:34:48,562
Then, let's complete
that ritual today itself.

1507
01:34:50,646 --> 01:34:55,146
-That ritual can only happen after a year.
-Okay, let's complete it today.

1508
01:34:55,604 --> 01:34:58,437
-Sister--
-I want to set him free…

1509
01:34:59,562 --> 01:35:01,021
as soon as possible.

1510
01:35:01,104 --> 01:35:03,062
-But Mom--
-Brother, listen.

1511
01:35:03,271 --> 01:35:04,146
Come on.

1512
01:35:04,562 --> 01:35:05,812
-Sit down.
-She's right.

1513
01:35:05,896 --> 01:35:06,771
Okay, then. Sit.

1514
01:35:06,854 --> 01:35:09,354
-What are you doing, sister-in-law?
-Please, sit.

1515
01:35:59,812 --> 01:36:00,937
Careful.

1516
01:36:02,479 --> 01:36:06,271
Look after your mother, son.
She's all alone now.

1517
01:36:06,354 --> 01:36:07,771
I'm still here, Laali!

1518
01:36:09,062 --> 01:36:10,271
Let's go.

1519
01:36:11,562 --> 01:36:12,896
Brother, drop them off carefully.

1520
01:36:14,229 --> 01:36:15,396
Thank God, they're gone.

1521
01:36:15,854 --> 01:36:17,729
Let's go. They're gone.

1522
01:36:17,896 --> 01:36:18,812
Let's go, Mom.

1523
01:36:18,896 --> 01:36:20,354
-That's mine.
-This is yours.

1524
01:36:20,437 --> 01:36:21,271
Hi!

1525
01:36:21,854 --> 01:36:23,271
You're glowing in pink.

1526
01:36:24,271 --> 01:36:26,396
-Are you leaving, Rahul?
-No, I just got here.

1527
01:36:35,562 --> 01:36:36,396
Take this.

1528
01:36:39,187 --> 01:36:40,396
We look nice together, right?

1529
01:36:42,646 --> 01:36:45,271
-When will you come back again?
-I don't know.

1530
01:36:47,812 --> 01:36:50,146
Hey, stop it! Are you crazy?

1531
01:36:50,229 --> 01:36:51,521
-I love you, Rahul.
-What?

1532
01:36:51,979 --> 01:36:53,104
I'm in love with you.

1533
01:36:53,646 --> 01:36:54,604
It's true love.

1534
01:36:55,896 --> 01:36:58,646
Before you go, just tell me
what you think of me!

1535
01:36:58,729 --> 01:37:00,354
-Bittu!
-I'll wait for you.

1536
01:37:00,437 --> 01:37:01,604
-What are you doing?
-Just tell me, Rahul--

1537
01:37:01,687 --> 01:37:02,687
What should I say?

1538
01:37:04,604 --> 01:37:06,604
Have you lost it? Grow up.

1539
01:37:07,479 --> 01:37:09,979
We're friends with benefits.
Do you understand what it means?

1540
01:37:10,604 --> 01:37:13,729
I'll see you if I come back,
but not every time.

1541
01:37:14,979 --> 01:37:15,937
What?

1542
01:37:17,104 --> 01:37:19,729
Why are you staring at me
as if I've betrayed you?

1543
01:37:19,812 --> 01:37:22,562
Two people just celebrated
New Year's Eve together. End of story.

1544
01:37:23,062 --> 01:37:24,812
What's the big deal?

1545
01:37:26,521 --> 01:37:28,937
Leave. Don't chew my brains.
I don't have time for this.

1546
01:37:35,354 --> 01:37:37,187
This time, the laddoos weren't that good.

1547
01:37:37,271 --> 01:37:41,021
Last year, they were just delicious.

1548
01:37:41,104 --> 01:37:42,812
I'd got them made under my supervision.

1549
01:37:42,896 --> 01:37:46,187
-Let me see.
-How can I eat them, then?

1550
01:37:46,271 --> 01:37:47,896
-What?
-They're too hard.

1551
01:37:48,729 --> 01:37:49,729
No problem.

1552
01:37:50,229 --> 01:37:52,937
When it'd be your turn,
we'll get the better ones.

1553
01:37:53,021 --> 01:37:55,812
-Oh, no.
-So, are you waiting for me to die?

1554
01:37:55,896 --> 01:37:56,979
I didn't mean that.

1555
01:37:57,312 --> 01:37:58,729
-But--
-Look at yourself!

1556
01:37:59,271 --> 01:38:00,687
You may die before me.

1557
01:38:02,521 --> 01:38:05,396
-Is your packing done, sister-in-law?
-Sulekha, listen.

1558
01:38:08,271 --> 01:38:11,146
I'm glad you're here.
What should we do about Mother-in-law?

1559
01:38:11,271 --> 01:38:12,812
Our husbands haven't decided anything.

1560
01:38:12,937 --> 01:38:16,312
We'll have to decide.
These brothers are totally useless.

1561
01:38:16,396 --> 01:38:17,854
-True.
-Isn't it their responsibility?

1562
01:38:17,937 --> 01:38:19,146
Must we do everything?

1563
01:38:19,937 --> 01:38:21,104
We're the daughters-in-law.

1564
01:38:21,271 --> 01:38:23,312
People will say that we
abandoned our mother-in-law.

1565
01:38:23,396 --> 01:38:26,646
Now, we'll have to look after
our husbands and their mother.

1566
01:38:26,771 --> 01:38:31,229
Listen, let's work it out over the phone.

1567
01:38:31,312 --> 01:38:34,312
-All right.
-Whoever has the time,

1568
01:38:34,646 --> 01:38:37,479
-can spend a few days here.
-I don't even have a minute to spare.

1569
01:38:37,646 --> 01:38:40,646
I can't have my children miss
school, and sit here.

1570
01:38:40,937 --> 01:38:44,229
As though I have time.
You know my husband's condition, right?

1571
01:38:44,312 --> 01:38:46,812
So, do you think I have
all the time in the world?

1572
01:38:46,937 --> 01:38:49,354
What about the fourth daughter-in-law?

1573
01:38:55,104 --> 01:38:58,229
Listen, what should we
do about Mom's loan?

1574
01:39:01,396 --> 01:39:04,521
Our parents never gave
us any responsibility.

1575
01:39:05,604 --> 01:39:08,146
That's why even we never
shouldered any responsibility.

1576
01:39:09,187 --> 01:39:11,437
For the first time,
we're getting to behave like adults.

1577
01:39:12,312 --> 01:39:13,646
We shouldn't miss this chance.

1578
01:39:14,604 --> 01:39:17,604
We will… always be there for her.

1579
01:39:18,562 --> 01:39:19,521
Let's go.

1580
01:39:20,104 --> 01:39:21,854
-Let's go.
-Give that to me.

1581
01:40:06,021 --> 01:40:07,729
Pay your respects to your aunt.

1582
01:40:08,062 --> 01:40:09,187
-No, it's fine.
-Hurry up.

1583
01:40:09,271 --> 01:40:11,229
Take him with you.

1584
01:40:11,354 --> 01:40:14,604
He keeps talking about you.

1585
01:40:15,104 --> 01:40:16,229
Do you want to go with her?

1586
01:40:16,479 --> 01:40:19,479
Seema, call us whenever you
get time from the shoot.

1587
01:40:19,562 --> 01:40:21,521
-Yes.
-Don't feel bad.

1588
01:40:21,854 --> 01:40:23,521
-Don't lose heart.
-We'll meet again soon.

1589
01:40:24,146 --> 01:40:26,104
-Goodbye.
-Yes, I have told him.

1590
01:40:26,187 --> 01:40:28,437
-Come for my birthday next year.
-Sure.

1591
01:40:28,521 --> 01:40:30,896
-Visit us in Agra.
-Keep in touch.

1592
01:40:30,979 --> 01:40:33,187
-We'll show you around.
-You packed everything, right?

1593
01:40:33,854 --> 01:40:35,729
-Yes.
-Now, I'll directly come to your wedding.

1594
01:40:37,437 --> 01:40:39,229
You should also visit
us during the holidays.

1595
01:40:47,562 --> 01:40:48,854
Sorry, Mom.

1596
01:40:50,187 --> 01:40:51,021
Bye, Auntie.

1597
01:40:51,979 --> 01:40:52,812
Bye, Paakhi.

1598
01:40:52,896 --> 01:40:55,271
-Hey, Paakhi!
-I'm coming!

1599
01:40:58,521 --> 01:40:59,812
Take care of yourself.

1600
01:41:02,646 --> 01:41:05,104
Take care of yourself.

1601
01:41:05,187 --> 01:41:06,396
Yes, I will.

1602
01:41:24,312 --> 01:41:25,562
Keep singing.

1603
01:41:26,896 --> 01:41:27,979
I'll give you a call.

1604
01:41:39,312 --> 01:41:42,354
I'll come back soon, Mom.

1605
01:41:44,437 --> 01:41:45,479
I'm always there for you.

1606
01:41:54,771 --> 01:41:56,104
Come on. I'll show you out.

1607
01:42:06,854 --> 01:42:07,854
Mom…

1608
01:42:12,604 --> 01:42:13,437
Mom…

1609
01:42:14,854 --> 01:42:19,854
our shop has been mortgaged,
so we can't sell it.

1610
01:42:21,437 --> 01:42:25,812
So, I was wondering-- In fact,
we all were wondering…

1611
01:42:27,062 --> 01:42:29,687
what if we sell the rest of the house…

1612
01:42:30,312 --> 01:42:33,646
except for this part?

1613
01:42:34,062 --> 01:42:35,937
We'd be able to repay
the loan from that money.

1614
01:42:36,062 --> 01:42:36,979
Yes, Mom.

1615
01:42:39,354 --> 01:42:41,979
You'll get lonely in this big house.

1616
01:42:42,062 --> 01:42:46,021
-Yes.
-How will you manage all the cleaning?

1617
01:42:46,979 --> 01:42:48,771
We won't be here to help.

1618
01:42:49,396 --> 01:42:50,354
-Right?
-Mom…

1619
01:42:51,062 --> 01:42:53,521
we can't arrange such
a huge amount in a short time.

1620
01:42:53,729 --> 01:42:56,479
We can't make this decision.

1621
01:42:56,562 --> 01:42:57,646
You must say something.

1622
01:42:58,146 --> 01:43:00,229
Mom, say something.
Why are you so quiet?

1623
01:43:03,229 --> 01:43:04,729
What are you thinking about?

1624
01:43:14,479 --> 01:43:18,562
You all should leave now.
It's time for your train.

1625
01:43:20,354 --> 01:43:23,437
You don't want to miss the train.

1626
01:43:59,771 --> 01:44:01,729
How is she going to manage
everything on her own?

1627
01:44:02,104 --> 01:44:03,812
She's hiding something from us.

1628
01:44:07,646 --> 01:44:09,354
She won't say what she feels.

1629
01:44:17,021 --> 01:44:18,771
-What's this? Show it to me!
-Hey--

1630
01:44:21,979 --> 01:44:25,396
The loan papers?
Are you going to pay the loan?

1631
01:44:25,854 --> 01:44:28,187
Stop blabbering!
Just have your tea!

1632
01:44:32,854 --> 01:44:35,687
Mom must have hidden
some money somewhere.

1633
01:44:35,854 --> 01:44:37,896
That's impossible!

1634
01:44:38,812 --> 01:44:42,521
Do you think she has a job? Nonsense!

1635
01:44:51,646 --> 01:44:53,187
It's all a sham.

1636
01:44:53,521 --> 01:44:56,812
Mom is very cunning.

1637
01:44:57,729 --> 01:44:59,521
She's kept her children in the dark.

1638
01:46:04,062 --> 01:46:04,937
Did you fix it?

1639
01:46:05,021 --> 01:46:07,187
Yes.
One chord was faulty.

1640
01:46:07,271 --> 01:46:09,771
I fixed it and it's playing well.

1641
01:46:10,104 --> 01:46:12,271
Great! Play something for me.

1642
01:46:32,104 --> 01:46:35,354
Our life is like the seven musical notes.

1643
01:46:35,937 --> 01:46:39,229
You have to find the note
that suits you fine.

1644
01:46:39,937 --> 01:46:45,187
When you find the note,
your life will become easy.

1645
01:46:46,104 --> 01:46:48,104
This life belongs to you.

1646
01:46:49,187 --> 01:46:50,979
So, the musical notes
should belong to you as well.

1647
01:46:51,062 --> 01:46:57,062
RAMPRASAD MUSIC SCHOOL

1648
01:47:00,187 --> 01:47:01,729
Welcome!

1649
01:47:03,187 --> 01:47:05,604
Namaste. Please come in.

1650
01:47:06,812 --> 01:47:09,354
Why didn't you come yesterday?

1651
01:47:09,896 --> 01:47:11,771
Namaste, my child.

1652
01:47:14,521 --> 01:47:16,021
Namaste.
